{"type":"message","id":"1a40fe0b","parentId":"82f945bb","timestamp":"2026-05-07T14:35:21.713Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why socraticode-code isn't being loaded/used every time or for analyzing whether work fits its criteria. They want it to be more proactive - either always loaded or checked automatically for every code task.\n\nLet me think about this. Currently, socraticode-code has this description:\n\n\"Use for any code task: codebase analysis, debugging, refactoring, feature work, scripts, tests, build failures, workflow inspection, symbol lookup, dependency tracing, or impact analysis. Prefer SocratiCode for all code-related reasoning before editing source.\"\n\nThe issue is that the skill's description tells me to use it, but the triggering is based on the skill description metadata. Let me check the current socraticode-code skill description to see if it's comprehensive enough.\n","thinkingSignature":"68dd935a3e326c72f5f0ab53a8e9589337cba492bcb32e77453efce013a5a092"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fubd7dsak3fd_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46672,"output":198,"cacheRead":96,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46966,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778164514157,"responseId":"064bd62405dd253b2e978df7d19107d2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e56d2070","parentId":"1a40fe0b","timestamp":"2026-05-07T14:35:21.760Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fubd7dsak3fd_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: socraticode-code\ndescription: \"Use for any code task: codebase analysis, debugging, refactoring, feature work, scripts, tests, build failures, workflow inspection, symbol lookup, dependency tracing, or impact analysis. Prefer SocratiCode for all code-related reasoning before editing source.\"\n---\n\n# SocratiCode สำหรับงานโค้ด\n\n## หลักใช้\n\nถ้างานเกี่ยวกับโค้ดทุกชนิด ให้ใช้ SocratiCode เป็นเครื่องมือหลักก่อนเสมอ:\n- อ่านภาพรวมโปรเจกต์ด้วย `codebase_context`, `codebase_status`, `codebase_graph_status`\n- หาโค้ดที่เกี่ยวข้องด้วย `codebase_search` / `codebase_context_search`\n- เจาะจงจุดทำงานด้วย `codebase_symbol`, `codebase_symbols`, `codebase_flow`\n- ตรวจผลกระทบก่อนแก้ด้วย `codebase_impact`, `codebase_graph_query`, `codebase_graph_circular`\n- ใช้ `codebase_index` / `codebase_update` / `codebase_watch` เมื่อดัชนียังไม่พร้อมหรือไฟล์เปลี่ยน\n\n## ลำดับทำงาน\n\n1. ระบุโปรเจกต์หรือพาธโค้ด\n2. ใช้ SocratiCode หาไฟล์ โหนด และเส้นทางการทำงานก่อนแตะโค้ด\n3. ถ้าเป็นการแก้บั๊ก ให้ค้นสาเหตุจาก symbol/flow/impact ก่อนเดา\n4. ค่อยแก้ไฟล์ด้วยเครื่องมือแก้ไขไฟล์\n5. ตรวจยืนยันด้วย SocratiCode ซ้ำถ้าต้องเช็กความสัมพันธ์หรือผลกระทบ\n\n## กติกา\n\n- อย่าเริ่มจากการเดาไฟล์โค้ดถ้าใช้ SocratiCode หาได้\n- ถ้าโปรเจกต์ยังไม่ถูก index ให้ index ก่อนค้นหา\n- ถ้าผลลัพธ์ไม่ชัด ให้ค้นซ้ำด้วยคำถามอื่นหรือขอบเขตที่แคบลง\n- ถ้างานไม่ใช่โค้ดจริง ๆ ไม่ต้องฝืนใช้สกิลนี้\n\n## ขอบเขต\n\nใช้กับ:\n- source code ทุกภาษา\n- scripts และ automation\n- workflow JSON / YAML / config ที่ควบคุมพฤติกรรมโค้ด\n- test, build, lint, dependency, architecture, refactor\n- การวิเคราะห์ผลกระทบก่อนลบหรือเปลี่ยนชื่อ\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778164521760}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb5fc754","parentId":"e56d2070","timestamp":"2026-05-07T14:35:48.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The boss is asking why SocratiCode isn't being automatically loaded/triggered every time, or at least analyzed to see if it matches before use. Looking at the description:\n\n\"description\": \"Use for any code task: codebase analysis, debugging, refactoring, feature work, scripts, tests, build failures, workflow inspection, symbol lookup, dependency tracing, or impact analysis. Prefer SocratiCode for all code-related reasoning before editing source.\"\n\nThe description is decent but it's not clear enough about WHEN to trigger. The boss wants it to be considered for every task. The problem is likely that the skill description in the YAML frontmatter is what OpenClaw uses to match the skill to user requests, and the current description might not be comprehensive enough or clear enough to trigger reliably.\n\n\nI'm realizing the real issue might be that the description uses qualifying language like \"for code task\" which makes it conditional, but what the boss actually needs is for SocratiCode to always be considered first as the primary analysis tool, with the decision about whether it applies made after loading. I should revise the description to be more directive and ensure it's treated as the default choice rather than a conditional one.","thinkingSignature":"bf2de4f90242db1c91d135b61ca4541cc306701e4d75078258944529cfdb2588"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n🧑🏼‍💻 เข้าใจครับ ปัญหาคือ description ติดเงื่อนไข \"for code task\" ทำให้บางที OpenClaw ไม่ trigger เพราะไม่แน่ใจว่าเข้าค่ายไหม\n\nผมแก้ description ให้กระชับและตรงประเด็นขึ้น — ระบุชัดว่าใช้ก่อนเสมอสำหรับงานทุกประเภทที่เกี่ยวกับโค้ด:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fks20vsy9qnn_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"description: |\n  Primary code analysis tool — MUST be loaded before reading, editing, or reasoning\n  about any code, scripts, automation, config files, or development tasks.\n  Triggers on: analyzing, debugging, editing, refactoring, creating, modifying,\n  inspecting, or tracing code; build failures; file exploration; symbol lookup;\n  dependency analysis; workflow inspection; impact assessment. Always use SocratiCode\n  first to search, trace, and understand the codebase before taking any action.","oldText":"description: \"Use for any code task: codebase analysis, debugging, refactoring, feature work, scripts, tests, build failures, workflow inspection, symbol lookup, dependency tracing, or impact analysis. Prefer SocratiCode for all code-related reasoning before editing source.\""}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1030,"output":655,"cacheRead":46752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48437,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778164521762,"responseId":"064bd62bcae5afc9a6cf4c7cb3202bd9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"790db8af","parentId":"bb5fc754","timestamp":"2026-05-07T14:35:48.632Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fks20vsy9qnn_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"  1 ---\n  2 name: socraticode-code\n- 3 description: \"Use for any code task: codebase analysis, debugging, refactoring, feature work, scripts, tests, build failures, workflow inspection, symbol lookup, dependency tracing, or impact analysis. Prefer SocratiCode for all code-related reasoning before editing source.\"\n+ 3 description: |\n+ 4   Primary code analysis tool — MUST be loaded before reading, editing, or reasoning\n+ 5   about any code, scripts, automation, config files, or development tasks.\n+ 6   Triggers on: analyzing, debugging, editing, refactoring, creating, modifying,\n+ 7   inspecting, or tracing code; build failures; file exploration; symbol lookup;\n+ 8   dependency analysis; workflow inspection; impact assessment. Always use SocratiCode\n+ 9   first to search, trace, and understand the codebase before taking any action.\n  4 ---\n  5 \n  6 # SocratiCode สำหรับงานโค้ด\n  7 \n    ...","firstChangedLine":3},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778164548632}}
{"type":"message","id":"886f6ba5","parentId":"790db8af","timestamp":"2026-05-07T14:36:02.254Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also let me check if there's an issue with the socraticode-code skill - the tool names like `codebase_context`, `codebase_search` etc. are listed in the available_skills in the system prompt. So SocratiCode is already loaded in the system prompt as tools. The skill just gives me instructions on how to use them.\n\nBut the key issue is that the AGENTS.md says to use SocratiCode before any code task. The skill's description now says \"MUST be loaded\" and lists all the trigger scenarios.\n\nThe real question from the boss is: why doesn't the system automatically trigger this skill for every code task? The answer is that OpenClaw skill triggering is based on the description keyword matching. So by making the description more explicit and using \"MUST be loaded\" language, plus listing ALL the trigger scenarios explicitly, it should improve the matching.\n\nLet me also verify the skill looks correct now.","thinkingSignature":"e207dc3592b7b22469924877c00e2a22bf56d13eef66950a4a812200176e32ce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3xp6zyljzeau_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw skills list 2>&1 | grep socraticode"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":272,"output":228,"cacheRead":47776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48276,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778164548634,"responseId":"064bd6466065b9b80e7c218952e69590"}}
