{"type":"message","id":"e902ae83","parentId":"1ab8b7b5","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:21:26.974Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"เช็ค limit OpenAI Codex ว่ากลับมารึยัง ต้อง update socraticode-code ดึงมาใช้ทุกครั้ง (already done). Now I need to check if Codex is back.\n\nSince this is about OpenAI Codex API availability and limits, I'll check the API.\n\nLet me check if codex is available (web search) and try the API directly.\n\n## Summary\n\n1. Already updated description. Now checking if OpenAI Codex is back - I should try the API to see the response, since there's no direct CLI command to check rate limits without making an API call. Let me try:\n","thinkingSignature":"667229eafcf0e07ff47fab41f3cdbd87b4870b4bbb11293fc6c411dc16270323"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z7vp12oxs0v1_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"OpenAI Codex API limit back available 2025"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z7vp12oxs0v1_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test Codex API directly\ncurl -s -X POST https://api.openai.com/v1/realtime/sessions \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $OPENAI_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"gpt-4o-mini\"}' \\\n  --max-time 10 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48474,"output":282,"cacheRead":96,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48852,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778167277934,"responseId":"064be0f0b080870aa36d4b305c6a1ca2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07bcf9f8","parentId":"e902ae83","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:21:28.405Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z7vp12oxs0v1_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenAI Codex API limit back available 2025\",\n  \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1076,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"duckduckgo\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c109944940d410cd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenAI Codex Usage Limits: Plus, Pro 5x/20x, Business Credits, and API ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"c109944940d410cd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://blog.laozhang.ai/en/posts/openai-codex-usage-limits\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fcbaf40b30b77776\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenAI Codex usage limits are currently a contract question, not one daily token number. Start by separating ChatGPT plan windows, Business or Enterprise credits, and API -key billing, then read the current limits for that branch.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fcbaf40b30b77776\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"blog.laozhang.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"54f81b7c7b248ee7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCodex - Usage after the limit reset update, single prompt eats 7% of ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"54f81b7c7b248ee7\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://community.openai.com/t/codex-usage-after-the-limit-reset-update-single-prompt-eats-7-of-weekly-limits-plus-tier/1365284\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"26620b56c79299f8\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWhen we see Codex's performance, especially for investigation—meaning autonomous research through the identification of relevant contexts—we can understand why the allowed token limit has changed. Indeed, it would be preferable to obtain transparency from OpenAI regarding the actual value of tokens per day/week.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"26620b56c79299f8\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"community.openai.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"af705e0f7c4a133e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCodex Usage Limits · openai codex · Discussion #2251 · GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"af705e0f7c4a133e\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openai/codex/discussions/2251\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1dd5adc1b3d4f212\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nCodex Usage Limits Hi @shanecowherd , This is exactly what I was wondering, so I made myself two .bat files that automatically switches to the (pay as you go) API key mode when i hit the usage limit and back to the Plusplan + GPT login mode once they let me 'out of jail' and my free usage resets. Happy to show how it works if you want.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1dd5adc1b3d4f212\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"83862fefaf214a17\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenAI Quietly Lowers Codex Usage Limit - and How to Run It Locally\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"83862fefaf214a17\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://articles.akadata.ltd/openai-quietly-lowers-codex-usage-limit-and-how-to-run-it-locally/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d82f362f7ece56d7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenAI Quietly Lowers Codex Usage Limit - and How to Run It Locally Tech‑Scroll 115 - \\\"When the river is dammed overnight, the wise redirect the stream.\\\" AKADATA 17 Sep 2025 • 6 min read\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d82f362f7ece56d7\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"articles.akadata.ltd\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09f456feb7491bc5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenAI Codex, ChatGPT Plus & Pro, and API Credits: The Complete 2025 Guide\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09f456feb7491bc5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.webdeveloper.today/2025/06/openai-codex-chatgptplus-pro-and.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a590734f6658e9ce\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAs of 3 June 2025 , OpenAI has started gradually rolling out the Codex agent to Plus subscribers, albeit with lower daily task limits than Pro. Plus does not include any metered API usage; your Plus fee pays for browser‑based consumption only. Codex impact: Good for occasional cloud editing sessions.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a590734f6658e9ce\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.webdeveloper.today\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"OpenAI Codex API limit back available 2025","provider":"duckduckgo","count":5,"tookMs":1076,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"duckduckgo","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c109944940d410cd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenAI Codex Usage Limits: Plus, Pro 5x/20x, Business Credits, and API ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"c109944940d410cd\">>>","url":"https://blog.laozhang.ai/en/posts/openai-codex-usage-limits","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fcbaf40b30b77776\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenAI Codex usage limits are currently a contract question, not one daily token number. Start by separating ChatGPT plan windows, Business or Enterprise credits, and API -key billing, then read the current limits for that branch.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fcbaf40b30b77776\">>>","siteName":"blog.laozhang.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"54f81b7c7b248ee7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCodex - Usage after the limit reset update, single prompt eats 7% of ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"54f81b7c7b248ee7\">>>","url":"https://community.openai.com/t/codex-usage-after-the-limit-reset-update-single-prompt-eats-7-of-weekly-limits-plus-tier/1365284","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"26620b56c79299f8\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nWhen we see Codex's performance, especially for investigation—meaning autonomous research through the identification of relevant contexts—we can understand why the allowed token limit has changed. Indeed, it would be preferable to obtain transparency from OpenAI regarding the actual value of tokens per day/week.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"26620b56c79299f8\">>>","siteName":"community.openai.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"af705e0f7c4a133e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCodex Usage Limits · openai codex · Discussion #2251 · GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"af705e0f7c4a133e\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openai/codex/discussions/2251","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1dd5adc1b3d4f212\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nCodex Usage Limits Hi @shanecowherd , This is exactly what I was wondering, so I made myself two .bat files that automatically switches to the (pay as you go) API key mode when i hit the usage limit and back to the Plusplan + GPT login mode once they let me 'out of jail' and my free usage resets. Happy to show how it works if you want.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1dd5adc1b3d4f212\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"83862fefaf214a17\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenAI Quietly Lowers Codex Usage Limit - and How to Run It Locally\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"83862fefaf214a17\">>>","url":"https://articles.akadata.ltd/openai-quietly-lowers-codex-usage-limit-and-how-to-run-it-locally/","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d82f362f7ece56d7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenAI Quietly Lowers Codex Usage Limit - and How to Run It Locally Tech‑Scroll 115 - \"When the river is dammed overnight, the wise redirect the stream.\" AKADATA 17 Sep 2025 • 6 min read\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d82f362f7ece56d7\">>>","siteName":"articles.akadata.ltd"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"09f456feb7491bc5\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOpenAI Codex, ChatGPT Plus & Pro, and API Credits: The Complete 2025 Guide\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"09f456feb7491bc5\">>>","url":"https://www.webdeveloper.today/2025/06/openai-codex-chatgptplus-pro-and.html","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a590734f6658e9ce\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAs of 3 June 2025 , OpenAI has started gradually rolling out the Codex agent to Plus subscribers, albeit with lower daily task limits than Pro. Plus does not include any metered API usage; your Plus fee pays for browser‑based consumption only. Codex impact: Good for occasional cloud editing sessions.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"a590734f6658e9ce\">>>","siteName":"www.webdeveloper.today"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778167288405}}
