{"type":"message","id":"b243e1e0","parentId":"b1ba9269","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:25:40.067Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The token is basically a Google OAuth token for ChatGPT Plus - it's not an OpenAI API key. So it's not something I can directly test against the OpenAI API.\n\nBut from the MEMORY.md, I know the boss has an API key from platform.openai.com. Let me look at all the API keys available and try each one.\n\nFrom earlier:\n- deepseek: sk-793970d...71d8\n- ollama-pay: sk-e53c34a...5ac4\n- ollama-claude: sk-5bb0c34...ee7c\n- openai: ... (masked)\n\n\n- openai-codex: eyJh... (JWT token, not an API key)\n- minimax: sk-cp-kjq0...vGyw\n\nThe only real OpenAI API key that could work is either the masked one or the ollama-pay key, but neither of those are actually for OpenAI's main API.\n","thinkingSignature":"3d2a1d773d88269a0196d19d07aa2ae5dea2135a476d8d586dd2189a08922a29"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uccgg3dnqzac_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nproviders=d.get('models',{}).get('providers',{})\n\n# check all openai-related providers\nfor name, prov in providers.items():\n    base = prov.get('baseUrl','')\n    key = prov.get('apiKey','')\n    if 'openai' in name.lower() or base.startswith('https://api.openai') or 'platform' in base.lower():\n        print(f'Provider: {name}')\n        print(f'  baseUrl: {base}')\n        print(f'  key: {key[:15]}...{key[-5:] if len(key)>15 else key}')\n        print()\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4254,"output":378,"cacheRead":61728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66360,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778167531732,"responseId":"064be1ee5688e77d6c5d42ae23fef0de"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9310004d","parentId":"b243e1e0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:25:40.116Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uccgg3dnqzac_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Provider: openai\n  baseUrl: https://api.openai.com/v1\n  key: ...\n\nProvider: openai-codex\n  baseUrl: https://chatgpt.com/backend-api\n  key: eyJhbGciOiJSUzI...cWI8c"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":34,"aggregated":"Provider: openai\n  baseUrl: https://api.openai.com/v1\n  key: ...\n\nProvider: openai-codex\n  baseUrl: https://chatgpt.com/backend-api\n  key: eyJhbGciOiJSUzI...cWI8c","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778167540116}}
{"type":"message","id":"612eae97","parentId":"9310004d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:25:43.497Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `openai` provider has an apiKey of \"...\" which is empty/masked. Let me check if there's an actual key stored somewhere. Maybe I need to look at the actual raw config.","thinkingSignature":"01fab21a8bf75d36ff8b3ee842fa665593088045148d76140e2f4886dbcbc0e5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f09xo9qc6lkp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check the raw config for openai provider key\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/home/apinan/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\nproviders = d.get('models', {}).get('providers', {})\nopenai = providers.get('openai', {})\nprint('openai apiKey:', repr(openai.get('apiKey', 'MISSING')))\nprint('openai baseUrl:', openai.get('baseUrl', 'MISSING'))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":280,"output":169,"cacheRead":65952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66401,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778167540119,"responseId":"064be1f533647a1dbe11dafbaa5f8ab0"}}
