{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:1060942816\",\n  \"message_id\": \"6466\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1060942816\",\n  \"sender\": \"▫️\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-05-07 22:36 GMT+7\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"▫️ (1060942816)\",\n  \"id\": \"1060942816\",\n  \"name\": \"▫️\",\n  \"username\": \"robberzaz\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"27a486c6","parentId":"0e312ee7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:36:55.165Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"cc70aa6f","parentId":"27a486c6","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:37:19.116Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants a real-time display on their computer screen showing CPU/RAM usage. Let me think about this...\n\nThey're on WSL2 and want a real-time overlay on their screen showing CPU/RAM percentages. Options:\n\n1. **GUI overlay on Windows** - Could use something like a lightweight tray app or terminal-based monitor\n2. **SSH into the machine** - But that's overkomplex\n3. **Simple console display** - htop, btop, etc.\n4. **Python script with loop** - Print to a persistent terminal window\n\nSimplest for WSL2: use `btop` or `htop` in a terminal window, or write a small Python script that updates in place.\n\n\nI could build a Python script that continuously displays CPU and RAM stats on a Windows machine by printing to a dedicated terminal window, or go simpler with just a basic batch script that loops and shows the metrics. The most straightforward approach for Windows is probably creating a compact script they can run in a minimized terminal. For a persistent overlay on the Windows desktop, I could write a Python script that displays stats in a title bar or use a lightweight tool like Conky on Linux, but on Windows a PowerShell loop running in a minimized console would be the simplest approach that works reliably across systems.\n\nSince they're using WSL2, I'm leaning toward a Python script using `curses` for terminal-based display, or a simple batch file with `ping` tricks to create a minimal overlay effect.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach for their setup is a Python script with `curses`—it'll display the stats directly in the terminal window with auto-refresh and look clean without external dependencies.","thinkingSignature":"50a2190776139f08c8360570415434f3807b4d51cecf488369f906a194048017"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nได้เลย ทำให้ดีกว่า 🧑🏼‍💻\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1lwgvilm7x8g_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Real-time CPU/RAM monitor — runs in terminal, auto-refresh.\"\"\"\nimport sys\nimport os\nimport shutil\nimport time\n\n# ── detect Windows─────────────────────────────────────────────\nIS_WINDOWS = os.name == \"nt\"\nif IS_WINDOWS:\n    import ctypes\n    kernel32 = ctypes.windll.kernel32\n\ndef get_cpu():\n    if IS_WINDOWS:\n        try:\n            kernel32.GetSystemTimes(ctypes.byref(ctypes.c_int64()),\n                                     ctypes.byref(ctypes.c_int64()),\n                                     ctypes.byref(ctypes.c_int64()))\n            # fallback: use psutil if available\n            import psutil\n            return psutil.cpu_percent(interval=0.1)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        return psutil.cpu_percent(interval=0.1)\n    except Exception:\n        # top fallback\n        out = os.popen(\"top -bn1 | grep 'Cpu(s)' | awk '{print $2}'\").read()\n        idle = float(out.strip().replace(',', '.')) if out.strip() else 0\n        return round(100 - idle, 1)\n\ndef get_ram():\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        m = psutil.virtual_memory()\n        return m.percent, m.used / (1024**3), m.total / (1024**3)\n    except Exception:\n        out = os.popen(\"free -h | grep Mem\").read().split()\n        if len(out) >= 7:\n            used = float(out[2].rstrip('Gi'))\n            total = float(out[1].rstrip('Gi'))\n            pct = int(used / total * 100)\n            return pct, used, total\n        return 0, 0, 0\n\ndef get_gpu():\n    if IS_WINDOWS:\n        try:\n            import subprocess\n            r = subprocess.run(\n                ['nvidia-smi', '--query-gpu=utilization.gpu,memory.used,memory.total', '--format=csv,noheader,nounits'],\n                capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=3\n            )\n            if r.returncode == 0:\n                gpu, mem_used, mem_total = r.stdout.strip().split(',')\n                return int(gpu.strip()), int(mem_used.strip()), int(mem_total.strip())\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    else:\n        try:\n            r = os.popen(\"nvidia-smi --query-gpu=utilization.gpu,memory.used,memory.total --format=csv,noheader,nounits\").read()\n            if r.strip():\n                gpu, mem_used, mem_total = r.strip().split(',')\n                return int(gpu.strip()), int(mem_used.strip()), int(mem_total.strip())\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    return None\n\ndef bar(pct, width=20):\n    filled = int(width * pct / 100)\n    return \"█\" * filled + \"░\" * (width - filled)\n\ndef clear_line():\n    print(\"\\033[2K\\033[0G\", end=\"\", flush=True)\n\ndef main():\n    interval = 1.0\n    try:\n        interval = float(sys.argv[1]) if len(sys.argv) > 1 else 1.0\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n\n    # Hide cursor\n    print(\"\\033[?25l\", end=\"\", flush=True)  # hide cursor\n\n    try:\n        while True:\n            cpu = get_cpu()\n            ram_pct, ram_used, ram_total = get_ram()\n            gpu = get_gpu()\n\n            # Update terminal title (works in most terminals)\n            title = f\"CPU {cpu:5.1f}% | RAM {ram_pct:4.1f}% | GPU {gpu[0] if gpu else 'N/A':>3}% | {time.strftime('%H:%M:%S')}\"\n            if not IS_WINDOWS:\n                print(f\"\\033]0;{title}\\007\", end=\"\", flush=True)\n\n            # Draw\n            line = (\n                f\"  CPU  {cpu:5.1f}% [{bar(cpu, 20)}]\\n\"\n                f\"  RAM  {ram_pct:4.1f}% [{bar(ram_pct, 20)}]  {ram_used:.1f}G / {ram_total:.1f}G\"\n            )\n            if gpu:\n                line += f\"\\n  GPU  {gpu[0]:3d}% [{bar(gpu[0], 20)}]  {gpu[1]}M / {gpu[2]}M\"\n            line += f\"\\n  {time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\"\n\n            clear_line()\n            print(line, flush=True)\n\n            time.sleep(interval)\n    except (KeyboardInterrupt, EOFError):\n        pass\n    finally:\n        print(\"\\033[?25h\", end=\"\", flush=True)  # restore cursor\n        print()  # newline\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n","path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":706,"output":1492,"cacheRead":65920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68118,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778168215165,"responseId":"064be4999c28265e721214837f4792cb"}}
