{"type":"message","id":"7c3de590","parentId":"74df22c0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:40:39.168Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The CPU calculation has a bug - the first reading is always 0, and subsequent readings are wrong. Let me fix the CPU calculation.\n\nActually the problem is that on the first call, prev_idle/prev_total are not set, so it returns 0. But subsequent calls - the delta calculation seems off. Let me check.\n\nActually the issue is that `get_cpu` returns negative values because the calculation is wrong. Let me debug this.\n\nThe `/proc/stat` line looks like:\n```\ncpu  user nice system idle iowait irq softirq steal guest guest_nice\n```\n\nBut my code splits `fields = line.split()` and then uses `fields[4]` for idle. \n\nIf the first field is \"cpu\", then fields[1] through fields[4] would be user, nice, system, and idle respectively - so fields[4] should be correct for the idle value. Let me trace through the math: on first call idle=100, total=500 so prev_idle and prev_total get set to those values and it returns 0. On second call if idle=120 and total=520, then d_idle=20, d_total=20, and the percentage should be (1 - 20/20) * 100 = 0%, but I'm getting negative values instead.\n\nWait, I'm seeing -98.5% which doesn't make sense. The calculation itself seems fine, so maybe the issue is that top is using a different method to calculate CPU usage than what I'm getting from /proc/stat - top might be averaging over a time window while I'm doing an instantaneous calculation, or there's something else about how the values are being read or compared that's causing the discrepancy. The RAM calculation is also showing 0.0% which is suspicious, and looking at the /proc/meminfo parsing, I think the problem is that \"MemAvailable\" might not exist on this system, so the fallback to \"MemFree\" isn't working correctly either. The first run showed 0.0% and then exit code 124 from timeout, so I need to trace through the logic more carefully to see where the calculation is actually breaking down. I'm computing the CPU percentage using delta values, and on the first call it returns 0 since there are no previous values. But the output shows -98.5%, which suggests the delta calculation is negative somehow. Let me trace through the math: if prev_idle is set to the idle value from the first read, then on the second call the delta should be the difference between current and previous idle, divided by the total delta across all fields. A negative result would only happen if the current idle is less than the previous idle, which shouldn't occur unless the values are being parsed incorrectly or the order of fields in /proc/stat is different than expected. I'm realizing the issue might be with how /proc/stat fields are parsed—the line contains 8 values representing different CPU times (user, nice, system, idle, iowait, irq, softirq, steal), and my calculation uses field[4] for idle time, which should be correct for getting the idle CPU percentage. The math seems right in principle, so I need to trace through the actual execution to see where it's breaking down. I'm realizing the issue might be with how the function captures and compares idle times across calls. On the first invocation the delta calculation returns 0, but on subsequent calls it's producing -98.5%, which suggests either the previous idle value isn't being stored correctly or the CPU stats are being read inconsistently. Let me trace through the actual values: if the first call sets prev_idle and prev_total, then the second call should calculate the difference between current and previous totals, but something in that sequence is clearly breaking down. I'm realizing the issue might be that `idle` is already subtracted from the total when I calculate `d_total`, so I'm essentially computing `(1 - (idle_diff / (total - idle_diff))) * 100`. Since idle_diff is always non-negative when idle increases (which it typically does), the denominator should be positive and the percentage should be reasonable—but maybe the values are just coming out mathematically strange, or there's something else going on with how the CPU times are being measured between the two reads. The calculation should work correctly—when d_total equals d_idle, we get 0% CPU usage, and when there's no idle time increase while total increases, we get 100%. Let me just rewrite the script from scratch to debug this properly.","thinkingSignature":"503da243a3c7bcc3c499f31c9dadd275b91f1f7d6a35e99f093fee7d44d88974"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nRAM คลาดด้วย แก้ใหม่:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o88y6kp5ttcj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /proc/meminfo | head -5\necho \"---\"\ncat /proc/stat | head -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":193,"output":987,"cacheRead":72576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73756,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778168417009,"responseId":"064be5628f2afa80e48c46c8ed3afafe"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b0cd5e25","parentId":"7c3de590","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:40:39.194Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_o88y6kp5ttcj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MemTotal:       24584928 kB\nMemFree:        13512664 kB\nMemAvailable:   20347256 kB\nBuffers:          260680 kB\nCached:          6255424 kB\n---\ncpu  1202765 5756 884757 72703598 67307 0 116153 0 0 0\ncpu0 168226 918 191108 12052498 14332 0 71918 0 0 0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":17,"aggregated":"MemTotal:       24584928 kB\nMemFree:        13512664 kB\nMemAvailable:   20347256 kB\nBuffers:          260680 kB\nCached:          6255424 kB\n---\ncpu  1202765 5756 884757 72703598 67307 0 116153 0 0 0\ncpu0 168226 918 191108 12052498 14332 0 71918 0 0 0","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778168439194}}
{"type":"message","id":"88d19665","parentId":"b0cd5e25","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:41:05.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MemTotal, MemFree, MemAvailable are in kB (not bytes or KB). The file uses \"kB\" suffix.\n- MemTotal: 24584928 kB\n- MemAvailable: 20347256 kB\n\nRAM = (24584928 - 20347256) / 24584928 * 100 = 17.2% (which is correct!)\n\nBut get_ram() returns 0.0% because the parsing is failing. Let me check:\n\n```python\nwith open(\"/proc/meminfo\") as f:\n    mem = {}\n    for line in f:\n        parts = line.split()\n        if len(parts) >= 2:\n            mem[parts[0]] = int(parts[1])\n```\n\nSo `parts[0]` would be `b'MemTotal:'`, `b'MemFree:'`, etc. and I'm looking for `b\"MemTotal:\"` which matches!\n\n\nFor CPU, the `cpu` line shows total=1202765+5756+884757+72703598+67307+0+116153 = 74944236 and idle=72703598. The first call has no prev values, so it returns 0. On the second call, the idle delta is 0 and total delta is 0, giving division by zero which explains the -98.5% reading.\n\nWait, but the idle should actually change between calls—I need to check the timing. Looking at the file format, the fields are `user nice system idle iowait irq softirq`, so idle is at index 4, meaning `int(fields[4])` extracts that value correctly. The real problem is that both calls happen within the same second, so the CPU usage hasn't had time to change.\n","thinkingSignature":"b5e497dceed60227f4d69dd9e6543799222eba4add1fc5ac8c0648a51ab2f4e7"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nCPU ติดลบเพราะ read ถี่เกิน — แก้ delta calculation ให้ robust ขึ้น:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uvvldc94mlv8_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Real-time CPU/RAM/GPU monitor — no external deps, pure /proc + shell.\"\"\"\nimport sys, os, time, subprocess\n\nIS_WINDOWS = os.name == \"nt\"\n\n# ── CPU via /proc/stat ──\n_prev_cpu = None\ndef get_cpu():\n    global _prev_cpu\n    try:\n        with open(\"/proc/stat\") as f:\n            line = f.readline()\n        # cpu  user nice system idle iowait irq softirq steal guest guest_nice\n        fields = line.split()\n        vals = [int(x) for x in fields[1:8]]\n        idle = vals[3]\n        total = sum(vals)\n        if _prev_cpu is not None:\n            d_total = total - _prev_cpu[0]\n            d_idle = idle - _prev_cpu[1]\n            pct = round((1 - d_idle / d_total) * 100, 1) if d_total > 0 else 0\n        else:\n            pct = 0\n        _prev_cpu = (total, idle)\n        return max(0, pct)\n    except Exception:\n        out = subprocess.getoutput(\"top -bn1 | grep 'Cpu(s)' | awk '{print $2}'\").strip().replace(',','.')\n        return round(100 - float(out), 1) if out else 0\n\n# ── RAM via /proc/meminfo ──\ndef get_ram():\n    try:\n        with open(\"/proc/meminfo\") as f:\n            data = f.read()\n        total = avail = 0\n        for line in data.splitlines():\n            parts = line.split()\n            if len(parts) < 2:\n                continue\n            k = parts[0].rstrip(':')\n            v = int(parts[1])  # kB\n            if k == \"MemTotal\":\n                total = v\n            elif k == \"MemAvailable\":\n                avail = v\n                break\n        if not avail:\n            for line in data.splitlines():\n                parts = line.split()\n                if len(parts) < 2:\n                    continue\n                k = parts[0].rstrip(':')\n                if k == \"MemFree\":\n                    avail = int(parts[1])\n                    break\n        if total:\n            return round((total - avail) / total * 100, 1)\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    return 0\n\n# ── GPU via nvidia-smi ──\ndef get_gpu():\n    try:\n        r = subprocess.getoutput(\"nvidia-smi --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits 2>/dev/null\").strip()\n        if r and r.isdigit():\n            return int(r)\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n    return None\n\n# ── Colour by load ──\ndef col(pct):\n    if pct >= 90: return \"#ff2222\"\n    if pct >= 70: return \"#ff8800\"\n    return \"#00ff88\"\n\n# ── Windows always-on-top overlay ──\ndef windows_overlay():\n    import tkinter as tk\n    root = tk.Tk()\n    root.overrideredirect(True)\n    root.attributes(\"-topmost\", True)\n    root.configure(bg=\"#1a1a2e\")\n\n    sw = root.winfo_screenwidth()\n    sh = root.winfo_screenheight()\n    W, H = 160, 80\n    root.geometry(f\"{W}x{H}+{sw-W-15}+15}\")\n\n    def drag_start(e): root._x, root._y = e.x, e.y\n    def drag_move(e): root.geometry(f\"+{e.x_root-root._x}+{e.y_root-root._y}\")\n\n    frm = tk.Frame(root, bg=\"#1a1a2e\", bd=0)\n    frm.pack(fill=\"both\", expand=True)\n    frm.bind(\"<Button-1>\", drag_start)\n    frm.bind(\"<B1-Motion>\", drag_move)\n\n    cpu_lbl = tk.Label(frm, text=\"CPU  --%\", font=(\"Consolas\", 13, \"bold\"), fg=\"#00ff88\", bg=\"#1a1a2e\", anchor=\"w\")\n    cpu_lbl.pack(fill=\"x\", pady=2)\n    ram_lbl = tk.Label(frm, text=\"RAM  --%\", font=(\"Consolas\", 13, \"bold\"), fg=\"#00ccff\", bg=\"#1a1a2e\", anchor=\"w\")\n    ram_lbl.pack(fill=\"x\", pady=2)\n    gpu_lbl = tk.Label(frm, text=\"GPU  --%\", font=(\"Consolas\", 13, \"bold\"), fg=\"#ff8800\", bg=\"#1a1a2e\", anchor=\"w\")\n    gpu_lbl.pack(fill=\"x\", pady=2)\n\n    def update():\n        cpu = get_cpu()\n        ram = get_ram()\n        gpu = get_gpu()\n        cpu_lbl.config(text=f\"CPU  {cpu:5.1f}%\", fg=col(cpu))\n        ram_lbl.config(text=f\"RAM  {ram:5.1f}%\", fg=col(ram))\n        gpu_lbl.config(text=f\"GPU  {gpu:3d}%\" if gpu is not None else \"GPU  N/A\", fg=col(gpu) if gpu is not None else \"#666666\")\n        root.after(1000, update)\n\n    root.after(500, update)\n    root.mainloop()\n\n# ── Linux/macOS terminal ──\ndef terminal_bar():\n    print(\"Real-time CPU/RAM/GPU  (Ctrl+C to exit)\")\n    print(\"=\" * 55)\n    while True:\n        cpu = get_cpu()\n        ram = get_ram()\n        gpu = get_gpu()\n        ts = time.strftime(\"%H:%M:%S\")\n        g = f\" | GPU {gpu:3d}%\" if gpu else \" | GPU  N/A\"\n        print(f\"\\r  [{ts}]  CPU {cpu:5.1f}%  |  RAM {ram:5.1f}%{g}     \", end=\"\", flush=True)\n        time.sleep(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if IS_WINDOWS:\n        windows_overlay()\n    else:\n        terminal_bar()\n","path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":205,"output":1796,"cacheRead":72736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74737,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778168439205,"responseId":"064be5797ed8ebc6eb968ec123689bfa"}}
