{"type":"message","id":"0ee21ac9","parentId":"b5d24385","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:42:00.005Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's working. Now let me create a shortcut for Windows that opens the overlay on top of everything. I need a way to show it as a proper always-on-top floating widget on the Windows desktop screen. \n\nFor Windows, the script uses tkinter which is available on the Windows Python installation. I need to create a .bat or .ps1 file to run it, and also create a shortcut.\n\nActually, let me think - the user is on WSL. The `IS_WINDOWS` check will be `False` because the script is running in WSL Python, not Windows Python. But if they want it to show ON THEIR WINDOWS DESKTOP, that's a different story.\n\n\nI should create a .bat file for Windows users to run the script using their Windows Python installation instead of WSL, so the tkinter overlay can actually display on their desktop.","thinkingSignature":"ab7878909c64c7ca5164f039c3e746a3b6cf7c260b220040847d77361419ded3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nใช้ได้แล้วครับ! ต่อไปจะทำให้ขึ้นบน Windows desktop จริงๆ\n\nแต่ต้องสร้าง shortcut แบบ **รันบน Windows Python** (ไม่ใช่ WSL) ถึงจะเห็น overlay บนหน้าจอได้\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zkhnz7yedbfe_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"@echo off\n:: SysMon — Real-time CPU/RAM/GPU overlay\n:: Run with: sysmon.bat\ncd /d \"%~dp0\"\npythonw \"%~dp0sysmon.py\" 2>nul\npause\n","path":"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/SysMon/sysmon.bat"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":220,"output":383,"cacheRead":74848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75451,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778168509810,"responseId":"064be5c0c5d8340619f2fe084821aa01"}}
