{"type":"message","id":"16cc00d6","parentId":"22b21660","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:44:33.163Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is tkinter not available in WSL Python. But when the script runs on Windows via `pyw`, it uses the Windows Python which should have tkinter bundled.\n\nBut wait - the script has `IS_WINDOWS = os.name == \"nt\"` which would be True on Windows. When copied to C:\\, the script would run on Windows Python where tkinter is available.\n\nThe problem might be that when running on Windows, the script can't find nvidia-smi (which is a Windows tool). Let me also check if python is available on Windows as `pyw`.\n\nActually, the bigger issue might be that the script ran but no window appeared. This could be because:\n\n\n1. pythonw runs with no console, so any errors get swallowed\n2. tkinter failed silently\n3. Or the process just didn't start at all\n\nI should write a test script that outputs to a log file so I can see what's actually happening when the script runs on Windows.","thinkingSignature":"9c8efea6f232e40a9c9ed18260b5bc363391cea13caa89b6b167ec54a84dfa8c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nขอบคุณที่บอกครับ — ปัญหาคือ `tkinter` ไม่มีใน Python ของ WSL ซึ่ง `pyw` บน Windows ก็ใช้ได้แต่อาจมีปัญหา silent fail\n\nลองเช็คก่อน:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y7oktss1q6wj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if Windows python has tkinter\n\"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python313/python.exe\" -c \"import tkinter; print('ok')\" 2>&1 || \\\n\"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python312/python.exe\" -c \"import tkinter; print('ok')\" 2>&1 || \\\n\"/mnt/c/Python313/python.exe\" -c \"import tkinter; print('ok')\" 2>&1 || \\\n\"/mnt/c/Python312/python.exe\" -c \"import tkinter; print('ok')\" 2>&1 || \\\necho \"not found\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":148,"output":469,"cacheRead":77248,"cache