{"type":"message","id":"b6b961f2","parentId":"6c66b2fb","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:47:15.496Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It ran successfully (exit code 1 is from the last echo pipeline, not from the PowerShell command). The process was running at pid 4924. So it works!\n\nNow the user says nothing shows on the screen. Let me think - the issue might be that on WSL2, `os.name == \"nt\"` is NOT true, because WSL2 is Linux. So the Python script runs in WSL2, not Windows.\n\nBut the script is meant to be run on Windows. The user double-clicks `sysmon.bat` which calls `pythonw.exe` (Windows Python). That should work.\n\nBut wait - maybe the issue is that when double-clicking, the current directory changes. Let me check if the script runs from a different directory.\n\n\nActually, I already tested this and it ran fine. The user might be double-clicking on the WSL side or there's a display issue. On WSL2 with tkinter, the DISPLAY environment variable might not be set, which could cause the tkinter window to fail silently. But we're running this on Windows Python, so that's not the issue.\n\nThe tkinter window should render correctly on Windows. I suspect the problem might be that the window is opening off-screen or in an unexpected location due to how `winfo_screenwidth()` and `winfo_screenheight()` behave in a headless or virtual display environment.\n","thinkingSignature":"81949bcd50e725a3f41bb19c07e1c4607aaaf98c91dbe2403a906aa1192d37bd"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nทดสอบแล้ว `RUNNING pid: 4924` — รันได้สมบูรณ์\n\nแต่หน้าต่างอาจถูกซ่อนหรืออยู่นอกจอ\n\nไฟล์นี้สำหรับรันบน **Windows** นะครับ — ไม่ใช่ WSL\n\nลองดับเบิลคลิกที่ `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\SysMon\\sysmon.bat` อีกครั้งไหม?\n\nถ้่ายังไม่ขึ้น ลองเช็คว่า Python เวอร์ชันไหนรันอยู่:\n\n```powershell\nC:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\pythonw.exe -c \"import tkinter; tkinter.Tk(); print('OK')\"\n```\n\nแล้วส่งผลมาได้เลยครับ 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthr