{"type":"message","id":"f975b24b","parentId":"90f77c09","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:55:56.393Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is WSL path conversion. Python is installed in WSL and running from the WSL path context. When we run Python from the Windows side, subprocess.getoutput() goes through WSL path conversion and tries to run nvidia-smi.exe but WSL doesn't have nvidia-smi in its PATH.\n\nActually, looking at the error messages, they're coming from the WSL side:\n```\n'\\\\wsl.localhost\\Ubuntu\\home\\apinan\\.openclaw\\workspace'\nCMD.EXE was started with the above path as the current directory.\n```\n\nThis means when PowerShell calls `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe`, Python is actually the WSL-hosted Python and the current directory is set to the UNC WSL path.\n \nThe real issue is that the sysmon.py script is running from the WSL path (mapped to `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\.openclaw\\workspace`) rather than Windows, so Python is actually the WSL Python installation, and subprocess.getoutput() doesn't have `C:\\Windows\\System32\\nvidia-smi.exe` in its PATH because it's running in the WSL environment.\n\nI could try running nvidia-smi directly through cmd.exe or use the WSL path `/mnt/c/Windows/System32/nvidia-smi.exe`, but the cleaner solution is to just use `shell=True` with the full Windows path to nvidia-smi.exe so the subprocess call works correctly.","thinkingSignature":"8a861f32292cc2c91d5cacc300a7e125e5cde8b65a6d432fb63c1da27b177f0a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rpeg7rpr1028_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"\"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/WindowsPowerShell/v1.0/powershell.exe\" -Command \"\n\\$py = 'C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe'\n\\$tmp = \\\"\\$env:TEMP\\\\gpu_test2.py\\\"\n@'\nimport subprocess, os\nprint('python:', os.__file__)\n# try shell=True with full path\nr = subprocess.getoutput('\\\"C:\\\\\\\\Windows\\\\\\\\System32\\\\\\\\nvidia-smi.exe\\\" --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits')\nprint('via shell:', repr(r.strip()))\n# try direct\nr2 = subprocess.getoutput('nvidia-smi --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits')\nprint('direct:', repr(r2.strip()))\n'@ | Out-File -FilePath \\$tmp -Encoding utf8\n& \\$py \\$tmp\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":246,"output":535,"cacheRead":91936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92717,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778169349113,"responseId":"064be9073ab10142b099713368baff29"}}
