{"type":"message","id":"e6b122c7","parentId":"9d73cc2c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:56:05.554Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5916poiwetm4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ── GPU ──\ndef get_gpu():\n    try:\n        if IS_WINDOWS:\n            r = subprocess.getoutput(r\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\nvidia-smi.exe --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits 2>nul\").strip()\n        else:\n            r = subprocess.getoutput(\"nvidia-smi --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits 2>/dev/null\").strip()\n        if r.isdigit(): return int(r)\n    except:"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"# ── GPU ──\ndef get_gpu():\n    try:\n        if IS_WINDOWS:\n            r = subprocess.getoutput(r\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\nvidia-smi.exe --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits 2>nul\").strip()\n        else:\n            r = subprocess.getoutput(\"nvidia-smi --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits 2>/dev/null\").strip()\n        if r.isdigit(): return int(r)\n    except:","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778169365554}}
{"type":"message","id":"547707ac","parentId":"e6b122c7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:56:13.298Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that WSL is set as the cwd, and subprocess.getoutput inherits that. When it runs `nvidia-smi`, it runs in WSL context which tries to use CMD on Windows but the path is wrong.\n\nThe solution: run nvidia-smi via cmd.exe explicitly on Windows.\n\nLet me try: `cmd /c nvidia-smi --query-gpu=...`\n","thinkingSignature":"9a2cc777afb407fab9d094459107ccecd931ece5eb2407d23fd273f8b97bc6a7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ip3jbbwn6l7p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"\"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/WindowsPowerShell/v1.0/powershell.exe\" -Command \"\n\\$py = 'C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe'\n\\$tmp = \\\"\\$env:TEMP\\\\gpu_test3.py\\\"\n@'\nimport subprocess, os\n# Use cmd /c to run nvidia-smi explicitly via Windows CMD\nr = subprocess.getoutput('cmd /c nvidia-smi --query-gpu=utilization.gpu --format=csv,noheader,nounits')\nprint(repr(r.strip()))\n'@ | Out-File -FilePath \\$tmp -Encoding utf8\n& \\$py \\$tmp\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":188,"output":256,"cacheRead":92544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92988,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778169365561,"responseId":"064be91667f44ed56242ed26fd5d8f16"}}
