{"type":"message","id":"f3ac8782","parentId":"37df1191","timestamp":"2026-05-07T15:56:18.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still failing with UNC path error. The issue is that WSL is somehow involved in the path somehow. Let me check if this is a WSL issue with Python's current working directory.\n\nActually, this is very strange. The error message says \"CMD.EXE was started with the above path as the current directory\" and \"UNC paths are not supported\". This means the Windows CMD is being started from the WSL UNC path `/mnt/c/...`.\n\nBut Python should be running in Windows! Unless... the Python is running through WSL as a symlink or something?\n\nLet me check if the Python installation is actually a WSL symlink.\n","thinkingSignature":"7700f0d994fa12baaaf17f18be66c36d1d32bea83b36ed73a4a8f5cb6a01d760"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_54yff8vy9294_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la \"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python312/python.exe\" 2>/dev/null\nfile \"/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/AppData/Local/Programs/Python/Python312/python.exe\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":267,"output":214,"cacheRead":92704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93185,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778169373807,"responseId":"064be91f3aba771b54212e83385043d9"}}
