{"type":"message","id":"08c67c04","parentId":"28257675","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:02:30.721Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue. In `get_gpu()`, when GPU is 0%, the top process might be the first one in the list (system process like dwm.exe, chrome.exe etc.) instead of the one actually using GPU. Also, the GPU process list shows processes but they might all have 0 GPU memory.\n\nLet me check:\n1. pynvml shows processes but they have 0 GPU memory (0 MB) - this means the GPU is not being used\n2. The top_name defaults to the first process in the list even if it has 0 memory\n3. When GPU usage is 0%, there's no meaningful \"top process\" - we should show \"---\" or \"idle\"\n\n\n4. But when GPU is actually under load, the processes with GPU memory should have real names\n\nI'm realizing the real problem: when GPU usage is 0%, the code still returns the first process from the list even though none of them are actually using the GPU. I need to filter to only show processes that have actually allocated GPU memory, and when GPU is idle, just display \"---\" instead.\n","thinkingSignature":"4acf19177672af6e1873e7327627e129ddf099230cf855dcde8e3b6e2db898ff"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_szetz5v4iew2_1","name":"socraticode__codebase_symbol","arguments":{"name":"get_gpu","projectPath":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1428,"output":280,"cacheRead":102304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104012,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778169740035,"responseId":"064bea8d3b684d213cb319ab1bdaa73b"}}
