{"type":"message","id":"148b4e74","parentId":"d798df82","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:02:43.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture. The problem is:\n\n1. **GPU name not showing** - `usedGpuMemory` is `None` for most processes (dw, explorer.exe etc use 0MB), so `mem > top_mem` (0 > 0 = False) never triggers, leaving top_name as \"---\"\n2. **CPU name wrong** - psutil's `cpu_percent(interval=0.05)` gives instant snap, not true load\n\nFix approach:\n1. For GPU: Instead of checking usedGpuMemory (which is None for most), use `nvmlDeviceGetProcessGraphicsRunningProcesses` or track actual GPU-using processes. Actually, the issue is just that most processes show 0MB. \n\nI need to use the actual compute processes that are using GPU memory rather than filtering by memory threshold, since dwm.exe likely has non-zero GPU usage even if the memory field is None.\n","thinkingSignature":"85aea4c7ee56670c57d9ec32b853f5dee70da6df1b0c502bc5e14089df96a5e0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dle20pkbf9w1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"\"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/WindowsPowerShell/v1.0/powershell.exe\" -Command \"\n\\$py = 'C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe'\n\\$tmp = \\\"\\$env:TEMP\\\\gpudebug.py\\\"\n@'\nimport pynvml, psutil\npynvml.nvmlInit()\nh = pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetHandleByIndex(0)\nprocs = pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetComputeRunningProcesses(h)\nprint('total processes using GPU:', len(procs))\nfor p in procs:\n    mem = p.usedGpuMemory\n    print(' pid:', p.pid, '| mem:', mem, '| type:', type(mem).__name__, '| bool:', bool(mem))\n    if mem and mem > 0:\n        try: print('   name:', psutil.Process(p.pid).name())\n        except: pass\npynvml.nvmlShutdown()\n'@ | Out-File -FilePath \\$tmp -Encoding utf8\n& \\$py \\$tmp\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":184,"output":456,"cacheRead":103712,"cacheWrite":0,"