{"type":"message","id":"5d93cc43","parentId":"67df7df2","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:04:14.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! So subprocess.getoutput('cmd /c nvidia-smi ...') works fine - it just captures the output. The problem is that WSL bash intercepts it and shows the warning, but the actual Python output is correct.\n\nSo the issue was that in sysmon.py when running on Windows, we call:\nsubprocess.getoutput(\"nvidia-smi ...\")\nBut on Windows, this is Python's subprocess which runs a shell - and the shell could be WSL's bash if there's a shell alias or something.\n\nActually no - on Windows, subprocess.getoutput() runs via cmd.exe by default. The output IS correct. \n\nWait - actually looking at the result above: subprocess.getoutput() with cmd /c returned \"2236, [Insufficient Permissions]\" - that's the actual nvidia-smi output. So it DOES work.\n\nSo in sysmon.py, if we use subprocess.getoutput('cmd /c nvidia-smi ...') it should work on Windows. The key is the 'cmd /c' to force Windows CMD.\n\nLet me update get_gpu_info() to use this approach.","thinkingSignature":"09516f10f4ecaf4724b234580b5f1546f6821ca31a0e83d005898ad7ee714d63"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_53kzcvbwu3a7_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"def get_gpu_info():\n    if not _init_gpu():\n        return None, \"---\"\n    try:\n        import pynvml\n        h = pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetHandleByIndex(0)\n        util = pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetUtilizationRates(h)\n        # Use nvidia-smi to get process names (pynvml pid list has no name field)\n        import subprocess\n        r = subprocess.getoutput('cmd /c nvidia-smi --query-compute-apps=pid,process_name --format=csv,noheader 2>nul')\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in r.strip().splitlines() if l.strip()]\n        names = []\n        for line in lines:\n            parts = line.split(',')\n            if len(parts) >= 2:\n                name = parts[1].strip()\n                if name and name not in ('[Insufficient Permissions]', '[N/A]'):\n                    # Shorten path\n                    if '\\\\' in name:\n                        name = name.split('\\\\')[-1]\n                    names.append(name[:20])\n        # dedup preserve order\n        seen = set()\n        unique = []\n        for n in names:\n            if n.lower() not in seen:\n                seen.add(n.lower())\n                unique.append(n)\n        return int(util.gpu), unique[0] if unique else \"---\"\n    except Exception:\n        return None, \"---\"","oldText":"def get_gpu_info():\n    if not _init_gpu():\n        return None, \"---\"\n    try:\n        import pynvml\n        h = pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetHandleByIndex(0)\n        util = pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetUtilizationRates(h)\n        # GPU processes — use name directly from nvml struct\n        gpu_procs = pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetComputeRunningProcesses(h)\n        names = []\n        for p in gpu_procs:\n            # name field available on compute process handle\n            name = getattr(p, \"name\", \"\") or \"\"\n            if name:\n                names.append(name[:20])\n        # deduplicate preserve order\n        seen = set()\n        unique = []\n        for n in names:\n            if n not in seen:\n                seen.add(n)\n                unique.append(n)\n        return int(util.gpu), \", \".join(unique[:2]) if unique else \"---\"\n    except Exception:\n        return None, \"---\""}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":244,"output":874,"cacheRead":108384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109502,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778169836963,"responseId":"064beaeebe199cbacc802308f1a723ff"}}
