{"type":"message","id":"3faf0e0d","parentId":"a7f4abd3","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:25:56.955Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the screenshot. The overlay shows:\n- CPU: 605% (wrong - that's per-core total, not system overall)\n- GPU: 5% (somewhat close to 0% shown in Task Manager)\n\nTask Manager shows:\n- GPU: 0% usage, 2.7/40 GB memory\n- CPU: 12% overall (not per-core)\n\nThe issue: `cpu_val` from psutil is accumulating percentages across ALL cores, so if a process uses 100% on 6 cores, it reports 600%. We need to normalize it.\n\nAlso the display is showing \"605%\" which is wrong. I need to fix the CPU percentage display.\n\n\nI'm realizing the confusion: the `cpu()` function returns the overall system CPU percentage as a single value, while `cpu_val` from `get_top_cpu_proc()` sums per-process percentages across all cores. The display is using `cpu_val` (605%) when it should be showing `cpu()` (12%). I need to swap which value displays as the main percentage.\n","thinkingSignature":"4839a703c34e583f9835f4339131efec95e40d9374c870f943bf7122178d44c2"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nเห็นปัญหาแล้วครับ! บรรทัดแรกโชว์ **605%** ซึ่งเป็น per-core total (ถ้า 6 cores คูณ 100% = 600+) — มันต้องโชว์ **12%** ตาม Task Manager\n\nกำลังแก้ให้ตรง Task Manager:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m8fzkhpb05pp_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"        cpu_lbl.config(text=f\"CPU : {cpu:.0f}%\", fg=pct_col(cpu))\n        cpu_name_lbl.config(text=f\"{cpu_name} {cpu_val:.0f}%\")","oldText":"        cpu_lbl.config(text=f\"CPU : {cpu_val:.0f}%\", fg=pct_col(cpu_val))\n        cpu_name_lbl.config(text=f\"{cpu_name}\")"}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1198,"output":476,"cacheRead":131136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132810,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"t