{"type":"message","id":"db1e3730","parentId":"416b1c68","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:29:47.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)` gives 10.9% which matches Task Manager's 12% (close enough).\n\nNow let me fix the code:\n\n1. `get_cpu_win()` → use psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)\n2. `get_top_cpu_proc()` → use psutil.cpu_percent() per process (no interval, uses previous sample)\n3. The issue was that overall CPU% was calculating wrong (53% instead of 12%)\n\nLet me fix.\n","thinkingSignature":"c9e592fe2646385b3ecbdde9ba7e7c0acc7548d310c16f06e77cbe255ccaf31c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nได้เลยครับ! ตอนนี้เจอสาเหตุแล้ว —\n\n**ปัญหา:** `GetSystemTimes` แบ่งตาม core → multi-core เลยคิดผิด\n\n**แก้:** ใช้ `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)` สำหรับ overall CPU จะตรง Task Manager\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5870irrqzw9h_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"def get_cpu_win():\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        return round(psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1), 1)\n    except:\n        return 0","oldText":"def get_cpu_win():\n    try:\n        k = ctypes.windll.kernel32\n        class FT(ctypes.Structure):\n            _fields_ = [(\"dwLow\", ctypes.c_ulong), (\"dwHigh\", ctypes.c_ulong)]\n        idle, kern, user = FT(), FT(), FT()\n        k.GetSystemTimes(ctypes.byref(idle), ctypes.byref(kern), ctypes.byref(user))\n        idle_t = idle.dwLow\n        total_t = idle.dwLow + kern.dwLow + user.dwLow\n        if hasattr(get_cpu_win, \"_p\"):\n            d = total_t - get_cpu_win._p[0]\n            p = (idle_t - get_cpu_win._p[1]) / d * 100 if d else 0\n        else:\n            p = 0\n        get_cpu_win._p = (total_t, idle_t)\n        return max(0, round(p, 1))\n    except:\n        return 0"}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":181,"output":545,"cacheRead":134336,"ca