{"type":"message","id":"c4f46902","parentId":"650a084e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:29:56.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now also fix the update loop - the interval sleep will block. Let me call cpu_percent without interval first time, then with 1 second interval subsequent calls. But the update() loop has a 1 second delay already, so that should be fine.\n\nActually, looking at the code: `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)` will block for 1 second every call. Since we call update() every 1 second, that's a problem. Let me use interval=0 (non-blocking) and just call it twice.\n","thinkingSignature":"224ef115d8f43b7e81a45a05259d2cc09c1b4e24af093d54b47491776cb303b7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oncf2x36fku6_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"_prev_cpu = None\ndef get_cpu_win():\n    global _prev_cpu\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        c = psutil.cpu_percent(interval=0)\n        if _prev_cpu is not None:\n            diff = c - _prev_cpu\n            # normalize: psutil returns per-core, cap at 100\n            pct = min(max(diff, 0), 100)\n        else:\n            pct = c\n        _prev_cpu = c\n        return round(pct, 1)\n    except:\n        return 0","oldText":"def get_cpu_win():\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        return round(psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1), 1)\n    except:\n        return 0"}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":386,"output":327,"cacheRead":134496,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135209,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778171387349,"responseId":"064bf0feac437bcfc64931dcd13564c2"}}
