{"type":"message","id":"e4f589b1","parentId":"c48d1fd0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:30:22.959Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually this approach is still wrong because I'm still calling `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)` which blocks for 1 second each call, freezing the UI.\n\nBetter approach: call once on first update (blocking 1s) then use the cached value from subsequent fast calls. But that's still slow.\n\nThe best approach for accuracy without blocking:\n1. On the very first call, block for 1s and return\n2. On subsequent calls, don't block - use the previous value we got\n\nBut since the update loop runs every 1s anyway, we could do:\n- Update 1: block 1s, get value, return\n- Update 2-∞: use cached value from 1s ago (acceptable)\n\n\n- On the first cycle, call `cpu_percent(interval=1)` and cache the result\n- On subsequent cycles, keep returning that cached value until the next update cycle\n- Each new cycle will call with interval=1 again to refresh the cache\n\nThis way I get an accurate reading without blocking the UI on every update.","thinkingSignature":"152d3c8666ef608f5b7058d2c6d43edd7472362293f0f666bda29db0fffe2ea2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8oc5yn4t5x0t_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"_cpu_cache = None\n_last_call_time = 0\ndef get_cpu_win():\n    global _cpu_cache, _last_call_time\n    import time as _time\n    now = _time.time()\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        if _cpu_cache is None:\n            # first call: block 1s to get initial reading\n            _cpu_cache = psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)\n            _last_call_time = now\n            return round(_cpu_cache, 1)\n        elif now - _last_call_time >= 1.0:\n            # at least 1s elapsed: fresh reading (block ~0.1s)\n            _cpu_cache = psutil.cpu_percent(interval=None)\n            _last_call_time = now\n        return round(_cpu_cache, 1)\n    except:\n        return 0","oldText":"_cpu_cache = None\ndef get_cpu_win():\n    global _cpu_cache\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        if _cpu_cache is None:\n            # first call: initialize, wait 1s\n            _cpu_cache = psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)\n            return round(_cpu_cache, 1)\n        else:\n            # subsequent: use cached value + get fresh\n            prev = _cpu_cache\n            _cpu_cache = psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)\n            return round(_cpu_cache, 1)\n    except:\n        return 0"}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":374,"output":594,"cacheRead":135104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136072,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778171410877,"responseId":"064bf1168ec67c31717e21ac2d7d900f"}}
