{"type":"message","id":"a15f626c","parentId":"abccfdac","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:32:22.480Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No real GPU-using processes. So gpu_name shows \"explorer.exe\" because explorer.exe appears first in the nvidia-smi list (but with [N/A] memory, meaning it doesn't actually use GPU). The issue is the filter isn't filtering out [N/A] entries well enough.\n\nLet me fix this: if all processes have [N/A] memory, we should show \"---\" not the first one.\n\nActually, the real issue is simpler: all processes in nvidia-smi compute apps have [N/A] because there's no actual GPU compute happening. But explorer.exe and other system processes show up as having a GPU context (even if not using it). So gpu_name = \"explorer.exe\" is misleading.\n\n\nI need to update get_gpu_info() to only include processes with actual GPU memory usage, and default to \"---\" when nothing's actively using the GPU.","thinkingSignature":"5dd59e6f0fd5eb7cc9da59d900f4f699a3960e5e89a7798249647f4773afb4dc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z5pabqqmk4s6_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"        r = subprocess.getoutput('cmd /c nvidia-smi --query-compute-apps=pid,process_name,used_memory --format=csv,noheader 2>nul')\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in r.strip().splitlines() if l.strip()]\n        names = []\n        for line in lines:\n            parts = line.split(',')\n            if len(parts) >= 3:\n                name = parts[1].strip()\n                mem = parts[2].strip()\n                if name and name not in ('[Insufficient Permissions]', '[N/A]') and mem not in ('[N/A]', '0'):\n                    if '\\\\' in name:\n                        name = name.split('\\\\')[-1]\n                    names.append(name[:20])","oldText":"        r = subprocess.getoutput('cmd /c nvidia-smi --query-compute-apps=pid,process_name --format=csv,noheader 2>nul')\n        lines = [l.strip() for l in r.strip().splitlines() if l.strip()]\n        names = []\n        for line in lines:\n            parts = line.split(',')\n            if len(parts) >= 2:\n                name = parts[1].strip()\n                if name and name not in ('[Insufficient Permissions]', '[N/A]'):\n                    if '\\\\' in name:\n                        name = name.split('\\\\')[-1]\n                    names.append(name[:20])"}],"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":187,"output":566,"cacheRead":137248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138001,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778171532994,"responseId":"064bf18e9ffb5fd7d6406de6d6818315"}}
