{"type":"message","id":"d4d5fbc4","parentId":"9b056f43","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:37:04.937Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - but blocking 1s on every update() call will freeze the UI. The update() runs every 1 second via after(1000). But since update() is the only thing running in mainloop(), the blocking call will work. But it will delay the UI update by 1 second each time. That's actually fine for this use case.\n\nActually, thinking more - the blocking interval=1 will work fine since the UI updates every 1 second anyway, and tkinter mainloop() handles it.\n\nLet me copy and run.","thinkingSignature":"7a97ffd5ff0bd46586e4545eecb74f546b5ff14c93b1a7cf5aa5e63c209f67b7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bezutw9l73wg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cp /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py /mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/SysMon/sysmon.py\n\n\"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/WindowsPowerShell/v1.0/powershell.exe\" -Command \"\nGet-Process pythonw -EA SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force\nStart-Sleep 1\n\\$proc = Start-Process 'C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\pythonw.exe' -ArgumentList 'C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\SysMon\\sysmon.py' -PassThru\nWrite-Host 'pid:' \\$proc.Id\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":303,"output":277,"cacheRead":142816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143396,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778171817723,"responseId":"064bf2ac2746f7a24b90f079f53e70d9"}}
