{"type":"compaction","id":"62070521","parentId":"1e5f8e31","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:54:22.394Z","summary":"\n## Goal\n1. Create an OpenClaw skill for the `ufo-gpt-image-gen` project\n2. Update `socraticode-code` skill to auto-trigger for all code tasks\n3. Check OpenAI Codex API usage limits\n4. Build a real-time floating CPU/GPU monitor overlay on Windows screen 2\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Window must appear on **monitor 2** (1536x864 at x=1536, y=0), **top-right corner** with 20px padding from edges\n- Overlay must use **always-on-top** mode (Tkinter `-topmost`)\n- Remove RAM row, keep only CPU + GPU + top process name\n- CPU% label (bold 16pt) and process name (12pt) on separate lines but aligned at same column\n- Background color `#111111`, CPU green/orange/red, GPU orange/red\n- GPU program name only shows when process has **actual GPU memory usage > 0 MiB** (filter out [N/A] and 0 entries)\n\n## Progress\n\n### Done\n- [x] Created `ufo-gpt-image-gen` skill at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/` with SKILL.md and references/verification.md\n- [x] Updated `socraticode-code` SKILL.md description to \"MUST be loaded before reading, editing, or reasoning about any code\"\n- [x] Created `sysmon.py` — floating tkinter overlay with CPU%, GPU%, top process name\n- [x] Installed `pynvml` into Python312 (`C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\pythonw.exe`)\n- [x] Window size 260x130, position x=2796, y=20 (monitor 2 top-right with 20px padding)\n- [x] GPU detection via `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetUtilizationRates()` + nvidia-smi compute apps\n- [x] Overall CPU via `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)` (system-wide, not per-core)\n- [x] Top CPU process via `psutil.process_iter()` + `cpu_percent(interval=0.1)`\n- [x] GPU process filter: only show processes with actual GPU memory > 0 MiB; show \"---\" when idle\n- [x] Window draggable\n- [x] Latest PID running: **5632**\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **CPU% mismatch** — overlay shows 12% but Task Manager shows ~57% (timing/sample difference)\n- [ ] **System Idle Process 582%** — shows system idle as top CPU process, which is misleading; should skip \"System Idle Process\"\n\n### Blocked\n- GPU process detection: when GPU util is 0%, all compute apps show `[N/A]` memory → filter returns \"---\" correctly\n- CPU timing: `psutil.cpu_percent()` and Task Manager sample at different moments, causing 1-2% drift\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **psutil over ctypes GetSystemTimes**: more accurate for system-wide CPU (GetSystemTimes is per-core on multi-core)\n- **pynvml for GPU%**: installed and working via Python312\n- **nvidia-smi `--query-compute-apps`** for GPU process names, filtered by memory > 0 MiB\n- **2 separate labels**: one for metric row, one for process name (same font/padding for alignment)\n- **Window 260x130** at x=2796, y=20 on monitor 2 (1536 offset + right-padding 20px)\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Fix CPU% sync**: sample CPU more frequently or average over longer window to reduce Task Manager drift\n2. **Skip System Idle Process**: filter out \"System\" / \"System Idle Process\" from top CPU process list\n3. **Verify GPU process** shows real GPU-using apps (ComfyUI, chrome.exe with GPU) when running AI tasks\n4. Update final `sysmon.py` to Windows desktop path and create permanent `sysmon.bat` shortcut\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Script path**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py` (Windows: `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\SysMon\\sysmon.py`)\n- **Python**: `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\pythonw.exe`\n- **Launch**: `pyw \"C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\SysMon\\sysmon.py\"` via PowerShell\n- **Monitor 2**: 1536×864 at x=1536, y=0 (from `System.Windows.Forms.Screen`)\n- **pynvml**: installed in Python312 — API `nvmlDeviceGetHandleByIndex(0)` + `nvmlDeviceGetUtilizationRates(h)`\n- **nvidia-smi**: `cmd /c nvidia-smi --query-compute-apps=pid,process_name,used_memory --format=csv,noheader`\n- **psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)**: blocks 1s on first call, then uses internal cache; gives system-wide 0-100%\n- **psutil cpu_percent per-process**: `interval=0.1`, returns per-core % (can exceed 100%)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n\n\n## Original Request\nUser reported a percentage mismatch: Task Manager shows CPU ~57% but the overlay shows only 12%.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Traced the root cause to psutil's `cpu_percent(interval=None)` returning a stale cached value instead of a fresh reading\n- An intermediate delta-based fix (`interval=None` with `cur - _prev_cpu`) also failed to produce correct readings\n- Final fix: replaced the entire `get_cpu_win()` with a simple blocking `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)` call — no caching, always fresh\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe final working version was copied to the Windows Desktop folder and launched via PowerShell (`pythonw.exe`). The old process was killed (`pid: 2020`). The assistant is now running/explaining the blocking 1-second approach.\n\n<read-files>\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/README ใช้งาน.txt\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/generate_bg.sh\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/gpt_background_image.py\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/start_chrome_bg.ps1\n~/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/SKILL.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/references/verification.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/SysMon/sysmon.bat\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"7ef62640","tokensBefore":162513,"details":{"readFiles":["/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/README ใช้งาน.txt","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/generate_bg.sh","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/gpt_background_image.py","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/start_chrome_bg.ps1","~/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md","~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/SKILL.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/references/verification.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/SysMon/sysmon.bat"]},"fromHook":false}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Continue from the current transcript after the latest tool result. Do not repeat the original user request, and do not rerun completed tools unless the transcript shows they are still needed.","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"6edd447a","parentId":"62070521","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:54:22.919Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"cb1fe8a6","parentId":"6edd447a","timestamp":"2026-05-07T16:54:40.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking: can we just read the values directly from Task Manager instead of calculating them? They want the numbers to match Task Manager exactly, so the simplest approach is to just read the values from Task Manager's data source directly.\n\nThe simplest way on Windows to get CPU% that matches Task Manager is to use WMI or Performance Counter - but the escaping issues from WSL are making this hard to test via PowerShell from WSL.\n\nLet me think about a completely different approach. Instead of running PowerShell from WSL (which has escaping issues), let me write a Python script that uses ctypes to call Windows API directly, or better yet, use the `psutil` library properly.\n \nActually, I just realized the real issue - when I call PowerShell from WSL using subprocess with shell=True, bash is eating the dollar signs in the Python string, which is why the PowerShell commands aren't executing properly. The WMI query worked fine when I tested it directly in PowerShell, so the problem is purely with how I'm invoking it from WSL.\n\nLet me try a different approach entirely - I'll use Python'sctypes to call the Windows API directly instead of going through PowerShell. I can use kernel32's GetSystemTimes to calculate CPU usage, which should be more reliable and won't have the escaping issues at all.\n","thinkingSignature":"cd7ee7bfed2918fbc0e59af2618cd4ea3e7f739d066318327d1ff0ca36cba11b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n3m5nst2fdey_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"\"/mnt/c/Windows/System32/WindowsPowerShell/v1.0/powershell.exe\" -Command \"\n\\$py = 'C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe'\n\\$tmp = Join-Path \\$env:TEMP 'ctypes_test.py'\nSet-Content -Path \\$tmp -Value @'\nimport ctypes, time\n\nclass FILETIME(ctypes.Structure):\n    _fields_ = [(\\\"dwLowDateTime\\\", ctypes.c_ulong), (\\\"dwHighDateTime\\\", ctypes.c_ulong)]\n\ndef get_system_times():\n    kernel32 = ctypes.windll.kernel32\n    idle = FILETIME()\n    kernel = FILETIME()\n    user = FILETIME()\n    kernel32.GetSystemTimes(ctypes.byref(idle), ctypes.byref(kernel), ctypes.byref(user))\n    idle_ns   = idle.dwHighDateTime * (2**32) * 10**7 + idle.dwLowDateTime * 10**7\n    kernel_ns = kernel.dwHighDateTime * (2**32) * 10**7 + kernel.dwLowDateTime * 10**7\n    user_ns   = user.dwHighDateTime * (2**32) * 10**7 + user.dwLowDateTime * 10**7\n    total_ns  = kernel_ns + user_ns + idle_ns\n    busy_ns   = kernel_ns + user_ns\n    return idle_ns, total_ns, busy_ns\n\nidle1, total1, busy1 = get_system_times()\ntime.sleep(1)\nidle2, total2, busy2 = get_system_times()\n\nidle_delta   = idle2   - idle1\ntotal_delta  = total2  - total1\nbusy_delta   = busy2   - busy1\n\nif total_delta == 0:\n    cpu = 0.0\nelse:\n    cpu = 100.0 * busy_delta / total_delta\n\nprint(int(cpu))\n'@ -Encoding utf8\n& \\$py \\$tmp\nRemove-Item \\$tmp -EA SilentlyContinue\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":45403,"output":744,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46339,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778172862919,"responseId":"064bf6c02e5c98acf48d68c75c95727c"}}
