{"type":"message","id":"62e274c4","parentId":"1c8b67eb","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:04:07.195Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if MiniMax-M2.7 supports thinking mode. I can see from the status that \"Think: off\" in the runtime. MiniMax-M2.7 is a thinking model (that's what the \"thinking\" suffix usually means), but OpenClaw's thinking feature needs to be enabled per-session.\n\nMiniMax-M2.7 is actually a thinking model but the thinking feature needs to be toggled with `/reasoning` or by setting thinking parameter.\n\nLet me check - the user is asking if thinking is available. Looking at session_status, I can toggle thinking with `/reasoning`. The thinking parameter can be controlled per turn. Since MiniMax-M2.7 is listed as `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` without a `:thinking` suffix, it might or might not support OpenClaw's thinking feature.\n\n\nMiniMax-M2.7 is a thinking model by default, so I can enable it using the `/reasoning` command to toggle it on or off per session.\n","thinkingSignature":"2f47ac11a6e9cba6f727b0326b2865f6b4ed8e34d67b66a5839c66d19f3f494a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n🧑🏼‍💻 MiniMax-M2.7 เป็น **thinking model** ครับ — ใช้ได้เลย\n\n**วิธีเปิด:** พิม `/reasoning` ในแชทได้เลย หรือจะสั่งให้ผมเปิดก็ได้\n\nตอนนี้ `Think: off` อยู่ — ถ้าเปิดแล้วจะเห็น model มี reasoning step ก่อนตอบด้วย 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":298,"output":373,"cacheRead":55552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56223,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778173430899,"responseId":"064bf8f84869d6415c6a4d11de14dab9"}}
