{"type":"message","id":"80b724c4","parentId":"e37d373d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:20:04.790Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to do a full test of the system to verify SocratiCode is working properly. Let me follow the exact steps I just set up in AGENTS.md:\n\n1. Load socraticode-code skill (read the SKILL.md)\n2. Verify SocratiCode works (call socraticode__codebase_about())\n3. Test codebase_search\n4. Test other SocratiCode tools\n\nLet me do this step by step.","thinkingSignature":"597dd36316900a4633d23ff81fb2947356ce1fcda32e8affc7bd8c0a2dd415fe"},{"type":"text","text":"ได้ครับเจ้านาย — ทดสอบเต็มรูปแบบเลย\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4sxv1yau4xqa_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":170,"output":174,"cacheRead":11865,"cacheWrite":69296,"totalTokens":81505,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778174396727,"responseId":"064bfcbf7b25ad234aef09e4c5292947"}}
{"type":"message","id":"10c68b73","parentId":"80b724c4","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:20:04.834Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4sxv1yau4xqa_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: socraticode-code\ndescription: \"Use for any code task: codebase analysis, debugging, refactoring, feature work, scripts, tests, build failures, workflow inspection, symbol lookup, dependency tracing, or impact analysis. Prefer SocratiCode for all code-related reasoning before editing source.\"\n---\n\n# SocratiCode สำหรับงานโค้ด\n\n## หลักใช้\n\nถ้างานเกี่ยวกับโค้ดทุกชนิด ให้ใช้ SocratiCode เป็นเครื่องมือหลักก่อนเสมอ:\n- อ่านภาพรวมโปรเจกต์ด้วย `codebase_context`, `codebase_status`, `codebase_graph_status`\n- หาโค้ดที่เกี่ยวข้องด้วย `codebase_search` / `codebase_context_search`\n- เจาะจงจุดทำงานด้วย `codebase_symbol`, `codebase_symbols`, `codebase_flow`\n- ตรวจผลกระทบก่อนแก้ด้วย `codebase_impact`, `codebase_graph_query`, `codebase_graph_circular`\n- ใช้ `codebase_index` / `codebase_update` / `codebase_watch` เมื่อดัชนียังไม่พร้อมหรือไฟล์เปลี่ยน\n\n## ลำดับทำงาน\n\n1. ระบุโปรเจกต์หรือพาธโค้ด\n2. ใช้ SocratiCode หาไฟล์ โหนด และเส้นทางการทำงานก่อนแตะโค้ด\n3. ถ้าเป็นการแก้บั๊ก ให้ค้นสาเหตุจาก symbol/flow/impact ก่อนเดา\n4. ค่อยแก้ไฟล์ด้วยเครื่องมือแก้ไขไฟล์\n5. ตรวจยืนยันด้วย SocratiCode ซ้ำถ้าต้องเช็กความสัมพันธ์หรือผลกระทบ\n\n## กติกา\n\n- อย่าเริ่มจากการเดาไฟล์โค้ดถ้าใช้ SocratiCode หาได้\n- ถ้าโปรเจกต์ยังไม่ถูก index ให้ index ก่อนค้นหา\n- ถ้าผลลัพธ์ไม่ชัด ให้ค้นซ้ำด้วยคำถามอื่นหรือขอบเขตที่แคบลง\n- ถ้างานไม่ใช่โค้ดจริง ๆ ไม่ต้องฝืนใช้สกิลนี้\n\n## ขอบเขต\n\nใช้กับ:\n- source code ทุกภาษา\n- scripts และ automation\n- workflow JSON / YAML / config ที่ควบคุมพฤติกรรมโค้ด\n- test, build, lint, dependency, architecture, refactor\n- การวิเคราะห์ผลกระทบก่อนลบหรือเปลี่ยนชื่อ\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778174404833}}
{"type":"message","id":"cf9ce475","parentId":"10c68b73","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:20:11.145Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, Step 1 done. Now Step 2 - verify SocratiCode works.","thinkingSignature":"96c4606b54b60b542348db33a8bc2dd6dd018e5a836c51965ff720b3e84e6c9d"},{"type":"text","text":"**Step 1 ✅** — Load skill แล้ว\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_acs0etuw6r47_1","name":"socraticode__codebase_about","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58228,"output":57,"cacheRead":24250,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82535,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778174404836,"responseId":"064bfcc7c692487aa29002541a1bab7b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee67c740","parentId":"cf9ce475","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:20:11.272Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_acs0etuw6r47_1","toolName":"socraticode__codebase_about","content":[{"type":"text","text":"SocratiCode — Codebase intelligence MCP server\nHybrid semantic + keyword search, dependency graphs, context artifacts.\n\nInfrastructure: ✅ All services running (Docker, Qdrant, ollama embeddings)\n\n━━━ Quick Reference ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\nIndexing:\n  codebase_index        — Index a project (background). Poll with codebase_status.\n  codebase_update       — Incremental re-index (changed files only).\n  codebase_stop         — Gracefully stop in-progress indexing.\n  codebase_remove       — Delete a project's index.\n  codebase_watch        — Start/stop/status of live file watcher.\n\nSearch:\n  codebase_search       — Hybrid semantic + BM25 search. Use after indexing.\n  codebase_status       — Check index status, progress, watcher state.\n\nDependency Graph:\n  codebase_graph_build  — Build AST-based dependency graph (background).\n  codebase_graph_query  — Imports & dependents for a file.\n  codebase_graph_stats  — Graph stats: files, edges, most connected, orphans.\n  codebase_graph_circular — Find circular dependencies.\n  codebase_graph_visualize — Mermaid diagram (default) or interactive HTML explorer (mode=\"interactive\"), colour-coded by language.\n  codebase_graph_status — Poll graph build progress.\n  codebase_graph_remove — Delete a project's graph.\n\nContext Artifacts:\n  codebase_context        — List artifacts (.socraticodecontextartifacts.json).\n  codebase_context_search — Search schemas, API specs, configs, docs.\n  codebase_context_index  — Re-index artifacts (usually automatic).\n  codebase_context_remove — Delete indexed artifacts.\n\nManagement:\n  codebase_health       — Check Docker, Qdrant, embeddings status.\n  codebase_list_projects — List all indexed projects.\n\n━━━ Typical Workflow ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n\n1. codebase_index → poll codebase_status until complete.\n2. codebase_search to find code. Search before reading files.\n3. codebase_graph_query to explore dependencies.\n4. codebase_context_search for schemas, API specs, configs.\n\nv1.8.8 · © 2026 Giancarlo Erra — Altaire Limited · AGPL-3.0\nhttps://github.com/giancarloerra/socraticode"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"socraticode","mcpTool":"codebase_about"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778174411272}}
{"type":"message","id":"4afd84e0","parentId":"ee67c740","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:20:15.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"SocratiCode is working. Infrastructure is ✅ all services running. Now let me test more tools.","thinkingSignature":"2c9ffc82efc0ddb09560e7943ebbcba7b0fae4c9c70408abcf052200ae708fef"},{"type":"text","text":"**Step 2 ✅** — SocratiCode ทำงานได้! Infrastructure ✅\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9byjoz5dtfwd_1","name":"socraticode__codebase_search","arguments":{"query":"sysmon.py CPU window overlay tkinter","projectPath":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace","limit":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58740,"output":113,"cacheRead":24250,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83103,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778174411275,"responseId":"064bfccc649961e831f70b37d3e03001"}}
{"type":"message","id":"566446c2","parentId":"4afd84e0","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:20:16.070Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9byjoz5dtfwd_1","toolName":"socraticode__codebase_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Search results for \"sysmon.py CPU window overlay tkinter\" (5 matches):\n\n--- sysmon.py (lines 157-215) [python] score: 1.0000 ---\n\ndef windows_overlay():\n    import tkinter as tk\n\n    root = tk.Tk()\n    root.overrideredirect(True)\n    root.attributes(\"-topmost\", True)\n    root.configure(bg=\"#111111\")\n\n    mon2_w, mon2_h = 1536, 864\n    W, H = 260, 130\n    x = 1536 + (mon2_w - W) - 20\n    y = 20\n    root.geometry(\"{0}x{1}+{2}+{3}\".format(W, H, x, y))\n\n    def ds(e):\n        root._x, root._y = e.x, e.y\n    def dm(e):\n        root.geometry(\"+{0}+{1}\".format(e.x_root - root._x, e.y_root - root._y))\n    root.bind(\"<Button-1>\", ds)\n    root.bind(\"<B1-Motion>\", dm)\n\n    font = (\"Consolas\", 16, \"bold\")\n    sub = (\"Consolas\", 12)\n\n    cpu_lbl = tk.Label(root, text=\"CPU : --\", bg=\"#111111\", fg=\"#00ff88\",\n                       font=font, anchor=\"w\", padx=10, pady=3, relief=\"flat\", bd=0)\n    cpu_lbl.pack(fill=\"x\")\n\n    cpu_name_lbl = tk.Label(root, text=\"---\", bg=\"#111111\", fg=\"#00ccff\",\n                             font=sub, anchor=\"w\", padx=10, pady=3, relief=\"flat\", bd=0)\n    cpu_name_lbl.pack(fill=\"x\")\n\n    gpu_lbl = tk.Label(root, text=\"GPU : --\", bg=\"#111111\", fg=\"#ff8800\",\n                       font=font, anchor=\"w\", padx=10, pady=3, relief=\"flat\", bd=0)\n    gpu_lbl.pack(fill=\"x\")\n\n    gpu_name_lbl = tk.Label(root, text=\"---\", bg=\"#111111\", fg=\"#ff8800\",\n                              font=sub, anchor=\"w\", padx=10, pady=3, relief=\"flat\", bd=0)\n    gpu_name_lbl.pack(fill=\"x\")\n\n    def update():\n        cpu = get_cpu_win()\n        cpu_name = get_top_cpu_proc()\n        gpu, gpu_name = get_gpu_info()\n\n        cpu_lbl.config(text=\"CPU : \" + str(cpu) + \"%\", fg=pct_col(cpu))\n        cpu_name_lbl.config(text=cpu_name)\n        if gpu is not None:\n            gpu_lbl.config(text=\"GPU : \" + str(gpu) + \"%\", fg=pct_col(gpu))\n            gpu_name_lbl.config(text=gpu_name)\n        else:\n            gpu_lbl.config(text=\"GPU : N/A\", fg=\"#888888\")\n            gpu_name_lbl.config(text=\"\")\n\n        root.after(1000, update)\n\n    root.after(500, update)\n    root.mainloop()\n\n--- sysmon.py (lines 216-228) [python] score: 0.6667 ---\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if IS_WINDOWS:\n        windows_overlay()\n    else:\n        print(\"CPU/GPU monitor (Ctrl+C to exit)\")\n        while True:\n            cpu = get_cpu_win()\n            gpu, gn = get_gpu_info()\n            cpu_name = get_top_cpu_proc()\n            g = \" GPU \" + str(gpu) + \"% (\" + gn + \")\" if gpu is not None else \" GPU  N/A\"\n            print(\"  \" + time.strftime(\"%H:%M:%S\") + \"  CPU \" + str(cpu) + \"% (\" + cpu_name + \")\" + g)\n            time.sleep(1)\n\n--- sysmon.py (lines 1-72) [python] score: 0.5000 ---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Floating CPU/GPU monitor — always-on-top overlay.\"\"\"\nimport sys, os, time, threading, queue\n\nIS_WINDOWS = os.name == \"nt\"\n\n# ── Windows CPU via ctypes GetSystemTimes (same source as Task Manager) ──\nif IS_WINDOWS:\n    import ctypes\n\n    class FILETIME(ctypes.Structure):\n        _fields_ = [(\"dwLowDateTime\", ctypes.c_ulong), (\"dwHighDateTime\", ctypes.c_ulong)]\n\n    _cpu_idle  = 0\n    _cpu_total = 0\n    _cpu_busy  = 0\n    _cpu_val   = 0.0\n    _cpu_lock  = threading.Lock()\n\n    def _init_cpu():\n        global _cpu_idle, _cpu_total, _cpu_busy\n        k32 = ctypes.windll.kernel32\n        i = FILETIME(); k = FILETIME(); u = FILETIME()\n        k32.GetSystemTimes(ctypes.byref(i), ctypes.byref(k), ctypes.byref(u))\n        _cpu_idle  = i.dwHighDateTime*(2**32)*10**7 + i.dwLowDateTime*10**7\n        _cpu_total = k.dwHighDateTime*(2**32)*10**7 + k.dwLowDateTime*10**7\n        _cpu_busy  = u.dwHighDateTime*(2**32)*10**7 + u.dwLowDateTime*10**7\n\n    def _sample_cpu():\n        global _cpu_idle, _cpu_total, _cpu_busy, _cpu_val\n        k32 = ctypes.windll.kernel32\n        i = FILETIME(); k = FILETIME(); u = FILETIME()\n        k32.GetSystemTimes(ctypes.byref(i), ctypes.byref(k), ctypes.byref(u))\n        idle_ns  = i.dwHighDateTime*(2**32)*10**7 + i.dwLowDateTime*10**7\n        kern_ns  = k.dwHighDateTime*(2**32)*10**7 + k.dwLowDateTime*10**7\n        user_ns  = u.dwHighDateTime*(2**32)*10**7 + u.dwLowDateTime*10**7\n        busy_ns  = kern_ns + user_ns\n        total_ns = idle_ns + kern_ns + user_ns\n        with _cpu_lock:\n            if total_ns > _cpu_total:\n                bd = busy_ns - _cpu_busy\n                td = total_ns - _cpu_total\n                _cpu_busy  = busy_ns\n                _cpu_total = total_ns\n                if td > 0:\n                    _cpu_val = 100.0 * bd / td\n\n    _cpu_t = None\n\n    def _cpu_thread_fn():\n        _init_cpu()\n        time.sleep(1.2)   # wait for first accurate 1s window\n        while True:\n            _sample_cpu()\n    \n\n--- sysmon.py (lines 73-89) [python] score: 0.3333 ---\ndef get_top_cpu_proc():\n    try:\n        import psutil\n        procs = []\n        for p in psutil.process_iter([\"name\", \"cpu_percent\"]):\n            try:\n                c = p.cpu_percent(interval=0.1)\n                if c > 0.5:\n                    procs.append((c, p.name()))\n            except:\n                pass\n        procs.sort(key=lambda x: x[0], reverse=True)\n        if procs:\n            return procs[0][1][:20]\n    except:\n        pass\n    return \"---\"\n\n--- sysmon.py (lines 90-102) [python] score: 0.3111 ---\n\n# ── GPU via pynvml ──\n_gpu_init_ok = False\ndef _init_gpu():\n    global _gpu_init_ok\n    if not _gpu_init_ok:\n        try:\n            import pynvml\n            pynvml.nvmlInit()\n            _gpu_init_ok = True\n        except Exception:\n            _gpu_init_ok = False\n    return _gpu_init_ok\n"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"socraticode","mcpTool":"codebase_search"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778174416070}}
