{"type":"message","id":"ecac96be","parentId":"d5308dc1","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:24:42.503Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f5ilqxvdsjbj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"5:  - Changing skill gating, allowlists, or load rules\n14:loads bundled skills plus optional local overrides, and filters them at\n19:OpenClaw loads skills from these sources, **highest precedence first**:\n28:| 6   | Extra skill folders   | `skills.load.extraDirs` (config) |\n34:per-agent Codex homes, so personal Codex CLI skills are not loaded implicitly.\n37:checkbox prompt before copying them into the current OpenClaw agent workspace.\n50:| Shared extra dirs    | `skills.load.extraDirs` (lowest precedence) | All agents on that machine  |\n84:    - The effective allowlist applies across prompt building, skill\n94:operating guides that are too long for the tool description but should be\n99:`skills.load.extraDirs`, so a same-named bundled, managed, agent, or\n161:- `openclaw skills install <slug>` is different — it downloads a ClawHub skill folder into the workspace and does not use the installer-metadata path above.\n162:- `skills.entries.*.env` and `skills.entries.*.apiKey` inject secrets into the **host** process for that agent turn (not the sandbox). Keep secrets out of prompts and logs.\n173:description: Generate or edit images via a provider-backed image workflow\n192:  prompt. The skill is still installed and can still be run explicitly as a\n207:OpenClaw filters skills at load time using `metadata` (single-line JSON):\n212:description: Generate or edit images via a provider-backed image workflow\n236:  Optional list of platforms. If set, the skill is only eligible on those OSes.\n254:  Optional installer specs used by the macOS Skills UI (brew/node/go/uv/download).\n257:If no `metadata.openclaw` is present, the skill is always eligible (unless\n269:- `requires.bins` is checked on the **host** at skill load time.\n278:description: Use Gemini CLI for coding assistance and Google search lookups.\n306:    - Gateway-backed installer selection is preference-driven: when install specs mix kinds, OpenClaw prefers Homebrew when `skills.install.preferBrew` is enabled and `brew` exists, then `uv`, then the configured node manager, then other fallbacks like `go` or `download`.\n312:    - **Download installs:** `url` (required), `archive` (`tar.gz` | `tar.bz2` | `zip`), `extract` (default: auto when archive detected), `stripComponents`, `targetDir` (default: `~/.openclaw/tools/<skillKey>`).\n361:  Optional allowlist for **bundled** skills only. If set, only bundled skills in the list are eligible (managed/workspace skills unaffected).\n365:keys). Config keys match the **skill name** by default — if a skill\n384:3. Builds the system prompt with **eligible** skills.\n391:eligible snapshot as a temporary Claude Code plugin and passes it with\n395:prompt catalog only.\n399:OpenClaw snapshots the eligible skills **when a session starts** and\n406:- A new eligible remote node appears.\n416:when `SKILL.md` files change. Configure under `skills.load`:\n433:OpenClaw can treat macOS-only skills as eligible when the required\n440:probes, OpenClaw clears its cached bin matches so agents no longer see\n445:When skills are eligible, OpenClaw injects a compact XML list of available\n446:skills into the system prompt (via `formatSkillsForPrompt` in\n450:- **Per skill:** 97 characters + the length of the XML-escaped `<name>`, `<description>`, and `<location>` values.\n455:total = 195 + Σ (97 + len(name_escaped) + len(description_escaped) + len(location_escaped))"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"5:  - Changing skill gating, allowlists, or load rules\n14:loads bundled skills plus optional local overrides, and filters them at\n19:OpenClaw loads skills from these sources, **highest precedence first**:\n28:| 6   | Extra skill folders   | `skills.load.extraDirs` (config) |\n34:per-agent Co