{"type":"message","id":"1e3b0c10","parentId":"f1be7970","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:39:45.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking to compare the OpenCode Go limits vs the native MiniMax API limits. Let me check what the MiniMax direct API limits are.\n\nFrom memory, the MiniMax API through thaigq (the provider we use) has its own limits. But I'm not sure what the exact limits are. Let me check the MEMORY.md or check the provider config.\n\nActually, looking at the session status:\n> 🔄 Fallbacks: ollama-pay/deepseek-v4-pro:cloud, ollama-pay/gemini-3-flash-preview:cloud, ollama-pay/qwen3.5-397b-cloud\n\n\n> 📊 Usage: 5h 45% left ⏱2h 27m\n\nThe \"Usage\" shown is specifically for the OpenCode Go subscription. I don't have the exact MiniMax direct API limits on hand, but the MEMORY.md file shows we use thaigq as the provider, so I should look there for their specific rate limits.\n\nSince I'm not entirely certain about the exact numbers, let me ask the user for clarification or look this up through OpenClaw's configuration.","thinkingSignature":"28a596cbc712a981223022f2d1294da60a08903c26ea15f1bb19759f67517cc5"},{"type":"text","text":"ผมไม่แน่ใจเรื่อง MiniMax direct API limit ครับ — ลองเช็คจาก config:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q4pa4d0x3xl1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config dump 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d.get('providers',{}), indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":170,"output":352,"cacheRead":93332,"cacheWrite":4513,"totalTokens":98367,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778175574523,"responseId":"064c0159363896786c1c7884e114fae8"}}
