{"type":"message","id":"3960463b","parentId":"2edb6ccc","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:40:06.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The models.json doesn't have minimax in it. The current setup uses `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` which is configured in the `agents.defaults.model` config, not through a separate provider API key.\n\nThe user is asking if OpenCode Go's limits are better or worse than the direct MiniMax API limits. \n\nThe key question is: do we have a direct MiniMax API key and what are its limits? From MEMORY.md:\n> Provider: thaigq (https://ollama-pay.thaigqsoft.com/api/v1)\n\nThis is the `thaigq` provider, not the official MiniMax API. \n\nI'm not certain what the thaigqsoft Ollama API limits are, so I should be straightforward about that. The MiniMax official API operates on a separate pricing structure with its own rate limits, distinct from what OpenCode Go offers. Let me search for more details on the actual MiniMax API constraints.","thinkingSignature":"2a2d75b8daa68d31c3a3e1f55689230ad764acda1a97b15165d2cb3bc723f0d1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_azm1jwwdc47w_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"MiniMax API rate limit requests per minute pricing 2025"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74363,"output":234,"cacheRead":24250,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98847,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778175597280,"responseId":"064c0170e438ee3ff468ca99d383e6ec"}}
