{"type":"message","id":"71cc86de","parentId":"64730327","timestamp":"2026-05-07T17:55:45.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking how much faster MiniMax is compared to local Qwen3.6 35B. Let me calculate based on the numbers I have.\n\n- Qwen3.6 35B with 16GB VRAM: ~30-40 tok/s\n- MiniMax M2.7 (server): ~50-100+ tok/s\n\nLet me use conservative numbers:\n- Qwen3.6: 30 tok/s\n- MiniMax: 60 tok/s (conservative estimate)\n\nThat's about 2x faster.\n\nBut actually, looking at OpenCode Go benchmarks, MiniMax M2.7 on their server might be even faster. \n\nLooking at those throughput numbers, MiniMax M2.7 hits around 3,400 requests per 5 hours, which translates to roughly 113 tokens per second if I'm doing the math right. The real performance advantage is probably closer to 3-4x faster than the local model when I factor in server-grade optimization.\n\nThe key insight is that tokens per second doesn't tell the whole story—latency matters too. A local model might have lower time-to-first-token since everything runs on your machine, but the actual generation speed on server-grade hardware with better connectivity is significantly faster. So MiniMax is probably 2-4x faster in practical terms.","thinkingSignature":"f10c2b3f355f9fd34392220ab8a038ca2a7f372a5a379de6d6428ee93bd112cd"},{"type":"text","text":"## 🔢 ความเร็วเทียบกัน:\n\n| | Local Qwen3.6 | MiniMax Server |\n|--|----------------|----------------|\n| **tok/s** | 30-40 | 50-100+ |\n| **เทียบกัน** | 1x | **~2-3x เร็วกว่า** |\n\n### 📐 ตัวเลข:\n\n```\nLocal Qwen3.6   →  35 tok/s (เฉลี่ย)\nMiniMax M2.7    →  75 tok/s (เฉลี่ย server)\n\n= MiniMax เร็วกว่า ประมาณ 2 เท่า\n```\n\n### ⏱️ ในการใช้งานจริง:\n\n| งาน | Local | MiniMax | ต่างกัน |\n|------|-------|---------|---------|\n| ตอบสั้น 50 tokens | 1.4 วิ | 0.7 วิ | ไม่รู้สึก |\n| ตอบยาว 500 tokens | 14 วิ | 7 วิ | **รู้สึกได้** |\n| เขียนโค้ด 2000 tokens | 57 วิ | 27 วิ | **รู้สึกชัด** |\n\n### 💡 สรุป:\n\n```\nMiniMax 