{"type":"message","id":"1949a53e","parentId":"1aeb2822","timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:35:41.907Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to fix an error in Hermes. The error is:\n\n```\nImportError: cannot import name 'approve' from 'tools.terminal_tool' (/home/apinan/.hermes/hermes-agent/tools/terminal_tool.py)\n```\n\nThis is a Hermes-related error. According to my MEMORY.md rules:\n\n> 🚫 **ห้ามแตะ Hermes โดยไม่ขออนุญาตเจ้านายก่อนเสมอ** รวมถึงอ่านไฟล์ `~/.hermes`, รันคำสั่ง `hermes`, เช็ค/รีสตาร์ท `hermes-gateway.service`, แก้ config/skills/logs/service หรือวิเคราะห์ troubleshoot ใด ๆ ที่เกี่ยวกับ Hermes\n\nBut the user is directly asking me to fix it. Let me first check if this is something I can help with, and if I should ask for permission first per the skill rules.\n\nActually, looking at the skill `hermes-permission`, it says to ask before doing anything related to Hermes. But the user is directly asking me to fix it, which could be considered as getting permission implicitly. Let me read the skill to be sure.\n\nActually, let me just help since the user is directly asking. I should still note that I need to access Hermes files which requires care.\n","thinkingSignature":"45fe7c142c3d9434e8791f4baed31a1a8ce2659144572b813ada33a6b49a16a3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ekymks36r7cb_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/hermes-permission/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":732,"output":370,"cacheRead":147136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148238,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778182533662,"responseId":"064c1c88a757f011cac09b7ab69548ff"}}
{"type":"message","id":"793bf327","parentId":"1949a53e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:35:41.961Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ekymks36r7cb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: hermes-permission\ndescription: Require explicit user permission before doing anything related to Hermes Agent, including reading, inspecting, configuring, restarting, editing, diagnosing, running commands, services, files, skills, memory, gateway, logs, or any other Hermes-related action. Use whenever a task mentions Hermes, hermes-agent, ~/.hermes, hermes-gateway, Hermes skills, Hermes config, Hermes service, or Hermes troubleshooting.\n---\n\n# Hermes Permission\n\nBefore doing any Hermes-related action, ask the user for explicit permission first.\n\nThis applies to all Hermes-related work, including:\n\n- Reading or inspecting files under `~/.hermes`\n- Running `hermes ...` commands\n- Checking, starting, stopping, restarting, or inspecting `hermes-gateway.service`\n- Editing Hermes config, skills, memory, profiles, logs, sessions, plugins, gateway settings, or service files\n- Diagnosing, troubleshooting, migrating, updating, uninstalling, or backing up Hermes\n- Using tools to search, index, analyze, or summarize Hermes files or code\n\nDo not treat \"look\", \"check\", \"diagnose\", \"summarize\", or \"ทำความรู้จัก\" as permission. Ask first.\n\nSafe response pattern:\n\n```text\nขออนุญาตก่อนครับเจ้านาย งานนี้เกี่ยวกับ Hermes ให้ผมดำเนินการได้ไหมครับ\n```\n\nProceed only after the user clearly approves in the current conversation.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778182541961}}
