ng approve {platform_name} {code}`\"\n4761:            # Accept /approve and /deny as shorthand for yes/no\n4763:            if cmd in (\"approve\", \"yes\"):\n4827:        # /approve, /always, /cancel (plus short aliases).  Anything else\n4833:        # precedence — /approve there unblocks the waiting tool thread.\n4834:        # Slash-confirm only catches /approve when no tool approval is live.\n4847:            if _cmd_reply in (\"approve\", \"yes\", \"ok\", \"confirm\"):\n4853:            elif _raw_reply.lower() in (\"approve\", \"approve once\", \"once\"):\n4855:            elif _raw_reply.lower() in (\"always\", \"always approve\"):\n5051:            # /approve and /deny must bypass the running-agent interrupt path.\n5055:            if _cmd_def_inner and _cmd_def_inner.name in (\"approve\", \"deny\"):\n5056:                if _cmd_def_inner.name == \"approve\":\n5057:                    return await self._handle_approve_command(event)\n5391:        if canonical == \"approve\":\n5392:            return await self._handle_approve_command(event)\n5565:        # Pending exec approvals are handled by /approve and /deny commands above.\n6588:            # thread blocks until the user responds with /approve or /deny, so by\n9261:            return EphemeralReply(\"⚡ YOLO mode **ON** for this session — all commands auto-approved. Use with caution.\")","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778182763070}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"eb260e4b","parentId":"0c9cd569","timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:40:18.247Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Create an OpenClaw skill for the `ufo-gpt-image-gen` project\n2. Update `socraticode-code` skill to auto-trigger for all code tasks\n3. Check OpenAI Codex API usage limits\n4. Build a real-time floating CPU/GPU monitor overlay on Windows screen 2\n5. **NEW:** Find SocratiCode-like tools that can identify and analyze problems precisely\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Window must appear on **monitor 2** (1536x864 at x=1536, y=0), **top-right corner** with 20px padding from edges\n- Overlay must use **always-on-top** mode (Tkinter `-topmost`)\n- Remove RAM row, keep only CPU + GPU + top process name\n- CPU% label (bold 16pt) and process name (12pt) on separate lines but aligned at same column\n- Background color `#111111`, CPU green/orange/red, GPU orange/red\n- GPU program name only shows when process has **actual GPU memory usage > 0 MiB** (filter out [N/A] and 0 entries)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Created `ufo-gpt-image-gen` skill at `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/` with SKILL.md and references/verification.md\n- [x] Updated `socraticode-code` SKILL.md description to \"MUST be loaded and used BEFORE reading, editing, or reasoning about any code, scripts, automation, config files, or development tasks. NEVER edit code without first searching and analyzing with SocratiCode.\"\n- [x] Updated AGENTS.md with mandatory SocratiCode workflow: (1) Load skill, (2) Verify SocratiCode works via `socraticode__codebase_about()`, (3) Fall back to exec/read/edit if fail + notify user\n- [x] Updated workspace `socraticode-code` SKILL.md with stricter rules: \"บังคับ: ต้องใช้ SocratiCode ก่อนแก้โค้ดทุกครั้ง — ห้ามข้าม\"\n- [x] Created `sysmon.py` — floating tkinter overlay with CPU%, GPU%, top process name\n- [x] Installed `pynvml` into Python312 (`C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\pythonw.exe`)\n- [x] Window size 260x130, position x=2796, y=20 (monitor 2 top-right with 20px padding)\n- [x] GPU detection via `pynvml.nvmlDeviceGetUtilizationRates()` + nvidia-smi compute apps\n- [x] Window draggable\n- [x] SocratiCode MCP health verified — Docker ✅, Qdrant ✅, Ollama ✅, version **v1.8.8** (latest)\n- [x] Gateway restarted with `minimax/MiniMax-M2.7` model, Think: **medium**\n- [x] OpenClaw skills list shows `socraticode-code` as ✓ ready, source: openclaw-workspace\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **CPU% mismatch** — overlay still shows different % than Task Manager. Attempted fixes: (1) blocking `psutil.cpu_percent(interval=1)`, (2) ctypes GetSystemTimes (gave 54% which matched), (3) thread-based with shared `_cpu_val` variable and `_cpu_lock`\n- [ ] **Find SocratiCode alternative tools** — user wants tools that can identify/analyze problems precisely; considering: SemaDB, CodeSense, Tabby, Continue.dev, CodeGPT, Rotten, Repogr, CodeRabbit AI, GitHub Copilot, JetBrains AI\n\n### Blocked\n- GPU process detection: when GPU util is 0%, all compute apps show `[N/A]` memory → filter returns \"---\" correctly\n- CPU timing: various approaches tried but % still doesn't match Task Manager exactly\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **psutil over ctypes GetSystemTimes**: more accurate for system-wide CPU (GetSystemTimes is per-core on multi-core)\n- **pynvml for GPU%**: installed and working via Python312\n- **nvidia-smi `--query-compute-apps`** for GPU process names, filtered by memory > 0 MiB\n- **2 separate labels**: one for metric row, one for process name (same font/padding for alignment)\n- **Window 260x130** at x=2796, y=20 on monitor 2 (1536 offset + right-padding 20px)\n- **ctypes GetSystemTimes**: tested and returned 54% matching Task Manager; later replaced with thread-based shared variable approach\n- **AGENTS.md forced SocratiCode workflow**: verified via `socraticode__codebase_about()` before any code work; fallback to exec/read/edit if MCP fails\n- **MiniMax M2.7 vs local models**: RTX 4060 Ti has **16GB VRAM** (not 8GB as initially misread), 48GB RAM\n- **DeepSeek-Coder-V3 Distilled**: best quality-per-GB for 16GB VRAM (12GB needed, 40.5% SWE-bench), but still can't solve hard problems well (~40% SWE-bench vs DeepSeek V4 Pro's ~60%)\n- **No local model matches DeepSeek V4 Pro intelligence** on 16GB VRAM — requires RTX 4090 24GB+ or server API\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Fix CPU% sync** with ctypes GetSystemTimes approach (verified working in standalone test: 54% matched Task Manager)\n2. **Verify thread-based `_cpu_val` approach** is returning fresh readings in actual sysmon.py overlay\n3. **Find SocratiCode-like alternatives** — search for tools: SemaDB, CodeSense, Tabby, Continue.dev, CodeGPT, Rotten, Repogr, CodeRabbit AI\n4. **Skip System Idle Process**: filter out \"System\" / \"System Idle Process\" from top CPU process list\n5. Update final `sysmon.py` to Windows desktop path and create permanent `sysmon.bat` shortcut\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Script path**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py` (Windows: `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\SysMon\\sysmon.py`)\n- **Python**: `C:\\Users\\Apinan\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\pythonw.exe`\n- **Launch**: `pyw \"C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Desktop\\SysMon\\sysmon.py\"` via PowerShell\n- **Monitor 2**: 1536×864 at x=1536, y=0 (from `System.Windows.Forms.Screen`)\n- **GPU**: RTX 4060 Ti — **16GB VRAM** (corrected from initial misread of 4GB)\n- **RAM**: 48GB (confirmed via PowerShell)\n- **pynvml**: installed in Python312 — API `nvmlDeviceGetHandleByIndex(0)` + `nvmlDeviceGetUtilizationRates(h)`\n- **nvidia-smi**: `cmd /c nvidia-smi --query-compute-apps=pid,process_name,used_memory --format=csv,noheader`\n- **SocratiCode MCP server**: `npx -y socraticode` via OpenClaw MCP config, version **v1.8.8**\n- **OpenCode Go limits**: MiniMax M2.7 at 3,400 req/5h, 17,000 req/month; MiniMax Official API has 500 RPM but costs per-token\n- **DeepSeek V4 Pro**: requires 512GB+ VRAM for local deployment — not feasible for consumer hardware\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user (▫️) asked the assistant to find tools similar to SocratiCode that can analyze code and point to problems accurately.\n\n## Early Progress\n- Assistant initiated a web search with query: \"code analysis AI tools like SocratiCode codebase intelligence finding bugs 2026\"\n- Search was executed via DuckDuckGo, returned 5 results\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe web search returned results (truncated in the suffix) about an AI & GenAI Specialist. The assistant needs to continue processing these search results to provide recommendations of code analysis tools similar to SocratiCode.\n\n<read-files>\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/README ใช้งาน.txt\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/generate_bg.sh\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/gpt_background_image.py\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/start_chrome_bg.ps1\n~/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md\n~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/SKILL.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/references/verification.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md\n/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py\n/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/SysMon/sysmon.bat\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"e346fa24","tokensBefore":153685,"details":{"readFiles":["/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/README ใช้งาน.txt","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/generate_bg.sh","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/gpt_background_image.py","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/Work Auto/ufo-gpt-image-gen/start_chrome_bg.ps1","~/.hermes/node/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md","~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/SKILL.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/plugin-skills/ufo-gpt-image-gen/references/verification.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/skills/socraticode-code/SKILL.md","/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/sysmon.py","/mnt/c/Users/Apinan/Desktop/SysMon/sysmon.bat"]},"fromHook":false}
